 be outfitted with a bigger active electronically scanned array (AESA) radar than the JF-17 Block 3 uses.\n\nThe aircraft can carry fourth-generation air-to-air missiles such as the short-range PL-10 and the beyond-visual-range PL-15.\n\nAccording to a foreign media report, China will deliver a total of 25 J-10C fighter jets to Pakistan, significantly increasing the country\u2019s military capability to defend airspace.\n\nRead more:\u00a0J-10C induction ceremony: Pakistan knows how to protect its boundaries, says Imran\n\nAfter being tested in Chengdu, the first batch of combat aircraft arrived in Pakistan a few days ago.\n\nImages of a Pakistan Air Force (PAF) J-10C fighter jet with the Pakistan Air Force (PAF) markings recently surfaced on social media and were widely circulated by media outlets.\n\nChinese analysts have praised the latest defence cooperation between China and Pakistan, saying that the move is significant for both countries because it strengthens the Pakistani military\u2019s combat capabilities, promotes China\u2019s aviation equipment, and serves regional security interests.\n\n\u201cThe J-10C will significantly improve the Pakistan Air Force\u2019s combat capabilities,\u201d Chinese analysts predicted.\n\n\u201cThe J-10C is a 4.5-generation medium-sized fighter jet that is more powerful than the China-Pakistan jointly developed lightweight fighter jet, the JF-17, which is currently in service with the Pakistan Air Force,\u201d Shi Hong, Executive Chief Editor of Shipborne Weapons, told the Global Times.\n\n\nDownload BOL News App for latest news","url":"https://www.bolnews.com/pakistan/2022/03/paf-formally-inducts-rafale-rival-china-made-j-10c-fighter-jets/"},"ca5d5316-4583-45b6-a00a-47c9c47c6d2f_739925080":{"id":"ca5d5316-4583-45b6-a00a-47c9c47c6d2f_739925080","text":"According to Turkish media reports, after the delay in delivery, Pakistan has decided to cancel its 2018 purchase of 30 T129 attack helicopters from Turkey, and switch to the purchase of Chinese-made Z-10ME armed helicopters, which can be said to be the dividends derived from Pakistan's purchase of Chinese-made J-10 fighters.\n\"Global Network\" quoted the local media \"Defense Industry News\" reported that the decision to cancel the purchase of Turkish attack helicopters was the head of the Public Relations Department of the Pakistan Armed Forces Babar.\nMajor General Iftihar announced it at a press conference.\nHe said Pakistan was \"determined to move forward\" and confirmed that talks were under way with China on the purchase of the Z-10ME armed helicopters and that the Turkish deal had been abandoned.\nThe report pointed out that Pakistan and China in 2014 and the procurement of the direct -10 negotiations.\nHowever, in 2018, Turkey ordered 30 T129 attack helicopters worth $1.5 billion from Turkey. Since the LHTEC-T800 engine for the helicopter is made in the United States, it must first obtain the US export license, but the United States has not responded, so Turkey has been unable to execute the order.\nTurkey and the United States have been engaged in lengthy negotiations on the implementation of the contract, trying to obtain an export license for the engine.\nNow, according to Pakistan, this process, which has been going on for many years, is over.\nIn an earlier statement, Turkish presidential spokesman Ibrahim Karin said, \"The United States has prevented us from providing combat helicopters to Pakistan.\"\nThis could lead to the transfer of tenders to China, and the loser would be the United States. \u201d\nAccording to earlier reports, in sharp contrast to Pakistan \u2019 s lack of a U.S. export license for its order, Turkey \u2019 s contract to sell the same attack helicopter to the Philippines was approved by the U.S. government.\nPakistan \u2019 s military plans to replace 48 old American-made AH-1F attack helicopters with new armed helicopters.\nPreviously, Pakistan had reached an agreement with the United States to purchase 12 new AH-1Z attack helicopters, but due to the problems of the United States, the agreement could not be implemented.\nAccording to public information, the Chinese-made Z-10ME is an advanced attack helicopter that debuted in 2018, and it is derived from the Z-10 upgrade, including: equipped with active and passive confrontation equipment, replaced with more powerful engines up to 1200 kW, new engine exhaust vents to reduce infrared features, and attached deck to provide defense capabilities.\nThe report pointed out that the Z-10ME has all-weather combat capabilities, with air-to-air missiles, rockets, artillery and other airborne weapons, which can effectively attack enemy ground fortifications, armored and non-armored moving targets, and aerial targets such as helicopters.\nIt is understood that Pakistan has purchased at least 25 J-10CE fighters from China, and the country's interior minister recently announced that these fighters will fly over the observation deck in formation at the celebration of Pakistan's Independence Day in March.\nThis batch of fighters is also the first export of the J-10 series, which is of great significance to the international market prospects of China's defense industry.\nSource: Turkish media: Pakistan cancels Turkish order to buy China direct -10ME, the loser will be the United States\n# Armed Helicopter # Wu Zhi - 10ME # Turkey # Pakistan # China","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2022-0000.json.gz:24096","uncompressed_offset":739925080,"url":"www.chinatimes.com/realtimenews/20220107004588-260409","warc_date":"2022-01-07T12:58:47.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:ca5d5316-4583-45b6-a00a-47c9c47c6d2f>","warc_url":"https://www.chinatimes.com/realtimenews/20220107004588-260409"},"created":"2022-01-07T13:35:36.000Z","lang":"eng"},"7662ae65-98c5-4a3f-9b24-83a5f9fb7a72_1044319203":{"id":"7662ae65-98c5-4a3f-9b24-83a5f9fb7a72_1044319203","text":"The American F-16...\nInformation on the Chinese J-10C fighter\n\u00a9 AFP 2023 / KARIM SAHIBChinese J-10 fighter\nFollow us via\nThe Chinese J-10 is touted as the best alternative to the US fourth-generation F-16, which has led some countries to consider acquiring it.\nChina has produced about 350 such aircraft since they entered service in 2005, according to Military Factory.\nThe aircraft has a single crew and is used by China and Pakistan and is designed for aerial combat missions with a variety of weapons.\nTurkey to replace F-16 with Chinese fighter jet\nPhotos & Videos\nWhat are the technical specifications of the J-10?\nLength: 15.5 meters.\nDistance between wings: 9.7 meters.\nHeight: 4.7 meters.\nWeight of empty aircraft: 9.7 tons.\nThe total weight of the aircraft is 18.5 tons.\nSpeed: 2,336 km / h.\nAltitude: 20,000 meters.\nRange: 1800 kilometers.\nWhat is the arming of the J-10?\nThe Chinese J-10 has six under-wing and five under-hull external suspension points that allow it to carry a large external payload of weapons, including air-to-air missiles, laser-guided bombs and other types of conventional bombs, as well as a 23 mm internal machine gun.\nThere are several versions of the aircraft, some with one seat and others with two seats for training tasks, including:\nThe J-10A is a single-seat multirole fighter.\nJ-10B: Marine version with twin-engine engines.\nJ-10C: An upgraded version of the B version with an electronic radar and infrared guidance system for missiles.\n\u00a9 AFP 2023 / WANG ZHAO Chinese J-10 fighter\nThe Chinese J-10 fighter.\nThe J-10C is an upgraded export version, which Turkey may acquire as a replacement for the U.S. F-16 fighter jets.\nEarlier, a Turkish presidential official said Ankara was expected to abandon the U.S. F-16 fighter jets due to the availability of a better alternative in the Chinese J-10 signal.\n\u00a9 SputnikWhat are the capabilities of the Chinese J-16 fighter?\nWhat are the capabilities of the Chinese J-16 fighter?\nNews Ticker\n0.\nTo participate in the discussion\nSig