{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T146","run_id":"chili","topic_id":"1031","task":"multilingual","request_id":"1031","narrative_id":"1031"},"responses":[{"citations":{},"text":"<think>"},{"citations":{},"text":"</think>"},{"citations":{"df6a4c09-f85a-477b-8611-4893c5d0e01e_494470718":1.0},"text":"Foreign investments in Africa require local participation ranging from 25% to 40% in development laws."},{"citations":{"df6a4c09-f85a-477b-8611-4893c5d0e01e_494470718":1.0},"text":"Investors fear having to give up an average localization percentage of 25%."},{"citations":{"df6a4c09-f85a-477b-8611-4893c5d0e01e_494470718":1.0},"text":"South Sudan's investment laws mandate 80% national workers in any company operating there."},{"citations":{"df6a4c09-f85a-477b-8611-4893c5d0e01e_494470718":1.0},"text":"African countries need to balance investment needs with local interests to ensure sustainable and beneficial investments."},{"citations":{"a5d99f5d-5340-4171-8450-24720fdfb69e_898064754":1.0},"text":"The African Development Bank (AFDB) plays a critical role in addressing Africa\u2019s infrastructure investment gap, estimated at over USD 100 billion annually."},{"citations":{"a5d99f5d-5340-4171-8450-24720fdfb69e_898064754":1.0},"text":"The AFDB focuses on digital, climate, energy, transport, health, education, and research sectors."},{"citations":{"d3d488a3-667e-4965-94b6-a4c836cac734_116239050":1.0},"text":"The AFDB facilitates partnerships between African entities and foreign companies through mechanisms like the Global Gateway initiative."},{"citations":{"d5cd3455-4d8c-4af4-aad1-bcd069e48757_550752729":1.0},"text":"The UK\u2019s Growth Gateway supports African-British partnerships, including projects in Ghana, Nigeria, and Senegal."},{"citations":{"d5cd3455-4d8c-4af4-aad1-bcd069e48757_550752729":1.0},"text":"The UK Growth Gateway has funded projects like Ghana\u2019s Kumasi Market expansion (\u00a3120 million) and emergency bridge construction in Ghana (\u00a340 million)."},{"citations":{"5bfeb426-e80d-45e0-9fc1-d9c7182c9abb_187276660":1.0},"text":"The UK\u2019s UKEF enabled a \u00a31.5 million deal for road construction in Ghana."},{"citations":{"d5cd3455-4d8c-4af4-aad1-bcd069e48757_550752729":1.0},"text":"The UK Growth Gateway promotes clean energy investments and two-way trade between African and British businesses."},{"citations":{"5d57ca5a-4029-4169-88f5-10cc6fe7901c_288412069":1.0},"text":"The AFDB and UK Growth Gateway are key organizations facilitating African-foreign partnerships, as demonstrated by their projects in Ghana, Nigeria, and Senegal."},{"citations":{"d5cd3455-4d8c-4af4-aad1-bcd069e48757_550752729":1.0},"text":"The UK Growth Gateway has established a partnership in Senegal to boost trade and investment."},{"citations":{"df6a4c09-f85a-477b-8611-4893c5d0e01e_494470718":1.0},"text":"Companies prioritize profit and community benefits, aiming to create jobs and contribute to development."},{"citations":{"df6a4c09-f85a-477b-8611-4893c5d0e01e_494470718":1.0},"text":"Governments should balance community and investor interests to attract foreign investment."},{"citations":{"df6a4c09-f85a-477b-8611-4893c5d0e01e_494470718":1.0},"text":"Africa\u2019s growing population and under-saturated markets make it an attractive investment destination."},{"citations":{"d3d488a3-667e-4965-94b6-a4c836cac734_116239050":1.0},"text":"The AFDB and UK Growth Gateway support infrastructure and economic collaboration through public-private partnerships."}],"answer":[{"citations":{},"text":"<think>"},{"citations":{},"text":"</think>"},{"citations":{"df6a4c09-f85a-477b-8611-4893c5d0e01e_494470718":1.0},"text":"Foreign investments in Africa require local participation ranging from 25% to 40% in development laws."},{"citations":{"df6a4c09-f85a-477b-8611-4893c5d0e01e_494470718":1.0},"text":"Investors fear having to give up an average localization percentage of 25%."},{"citations":{"df6a4c09-f85a-477b-8611-4893c5d0e01e_494470718":1.0},"text":"South