{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T146","run_id":"chili","topic_id":"1043","task":"multilingual","request_id":"1043","narrative_id":"1043"},"responses":[{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"The Little Mermaid statue in Copenhagen, created by sculptor Edvard Eriksen in 1913, has faced repeated vandalism over the years, with notable incidents including theft, destruction, and graffiti."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"In 1964, the head of the statue was stolen, marking the first recorded act of vandalism."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"The head was stolen again in 1998, but it was later restored, though the motive behind this act remains unspecified."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"In 2003, the statue was blown up, knocking it off its base and causing it to fall into the bay, an act described as an \"act of vandalism\" without further details on the perpetrators or their motivations."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"The statue was doused in red paint in 2017 as part of a protest against whale hunting, a clear indication of a societal factor driving the vandalism."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"During worldwide protests after the death of George Floyd, the words \"racist fish\" were painted on the base of the statue in 2020, reflecting the broader societal context of anti-racism movements."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"The 2020 incident is explicitly perceived as a sign of support for the Kremlin in the Ukrainian conflict, highlighting a societal factor tied to political alignment."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"The statue has also been targeted with graffiti or signatures, though the specific motivations behind these acts are not detailed in the provided documents."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"The 2017 and 2020 incidents demonstrate direct links to environmentalism and anti-racism movements, respectively, underscoring the societal drivers behind these acts of vandalism."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"Earlier incidents, such as the 1998 theft and 2003 explosion, lack explicit motivations, suggesting they may be attributed to general vandalism or political statements, though this is not verified in the provided sources."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"The Little Mermaid statue in Copenhagen, created by sculptor Edvard Eriksen in 1913, has faced repeated vandalism over the years, with notable incidents including theft, destruction, and graffiti."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"In 1964, the head of the statue was stolen, marking the first recorded act of vandalism."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"The head was stolen again in 1998, but it was later restored, though the motive behind this act remains unspecified."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"In 2003, the statue was blown up, knocking it off its base and causing it to fall into the bay, an act described as an \"act of vandalism\" without further details on the perpetrators or their motivations."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"The statue was doused in red paint in 2017 as part of a protest against whale hunting, a clear indication of a societal factor driving the vandalism."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"During worldwide protests after the death of George Floyd, the words \"racist fish\" were painted on the base of the statue in 2020, reflecting the broader societal context of anti-racism movements."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"The 2020 incident is explicitly perceived as a sign of support for the Kremlin in the Ukrainian conflict, highlighting a societal factor tied to political alignment."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"The statue has also been targeted with graffiti or signatures, though the specific motivations behind these acts are not detailed in the provided documents."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"The 2017 and 2020 incidents demonstrate direct links to environmentalism and anti-racism movements, respectively, underscoring the societal drivers behind these acts of vandalism."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"Earlier incidents, such as the 1998 theft and 2003 explosion, lack explicit motivations, suggesting they may be attributed to general vandalism or political statements, though this is not verified in the provided sources."}],"references":["4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268"],"documents":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":{"id":"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268","text":"Unknown people draw Russian flag on a statue of a mermaid in Copenhagen\nCOPENHAGEN (AFP) - The iconic Little Mermaid statue in the Danish capital Copenhagen was vandalized on Wednesday night as unidentified people painted the Russian flag on its base.\nAnnouncement\nAn AFP correspondent reported that the Russian flag was painted under unknown circumstances on the stone above which a statue of the Little Mermaid, inspired by the heroine of one of the stories of the writer Hans Christian Andersen, was installed.\nDanish police said they were launching an investigation into the incident, without giving any indication of the source of the move, which shows clear support for Russia amid the ongoing war in Ukraine.\nA Copenhagen police spokesman told AFP: \"We are investigating the area in order to find any evidence.\"\nA small number of tourists in the area took pictures of the statue in the port of Copenhagen, which was vandalized on Thursday morning.\nThe Little Mermaid statue on a largely unfrequented promenade has been targeted several times since it was installed in 1913.\nIn 1964, the head of the nymph was stolen for the first time without being recovered.\nIn 1998, a group of vandals cut off the head of the statue again, but it was later restored.\nThis monument was exposed to the explosion in 2003.\nThe statue, created by Danish sculptor Edvard Eriksen, has also been targeted several times with graffiti or graffiti, most recently in 2020 with the inscription \u201cracist fish \u201d.","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2023-0006.json.gz:38440","uncompressed_offset":592630268,"url":"www.france24.com/ar/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%85%D8%B1%D8%A9/20230302-%D9%85%D8%AC%D9%87%D9%88%D9%84%D9%88%D9%86-%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%85%D9%88%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B3%D9%8A-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%AA%D9%85%D8%AB%D8%A7%D9%84-%D8%AD%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%AD%D8%B1-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D9%83%D9%88%D8%A8%D9%86%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%BA%D9%86","warc_date":"2023-03-03T12:29:55.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4>","warc_url":"https://www.france24.com/ar/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%85%D8%B1%D8%A9/20230302-%D9%85%D8%AC%D9%87%D9%88%D9%84%D9%88%D9%86-%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%85%D9%88%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B3%D9%8A-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%AA%D9%85%D8%AB%D8%A7%D9%84-%D8%AD%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%AD%D8%B1-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D9%83%D9%88%D8%A8%D9%86%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%BA%D9%86"},"created":"2023-03-03T12:51:55.000Z","lang":"eng"}}}
