s behind these acts are not detailed in the provided documents."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"The 2017 and 2020 incidents demonstrate direct links to environmentalism and anti-racism movements, respectively, underscoring the societal drivers behind these acts of vandalism."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"Earlier incidents, such as the 1998 theft and 2003 explosion, lack explicit motivations, suggesting they may be attributed to general vandalism or political statements, though this is not verified in the provided sources."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"The Little Mermaid statue in Copenhagen, created by sculptor Edvard Eriksen in 1913, has faced repeated vandalism over the years, with notable incidents including theft, destruction, and graffiti."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"In 1964, the head of the statue was stolen, marking the first recorded act of vandalism."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"The head was stolen again in 1998, but it was later restored, though the motive behind this act remains unspecified."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"In 2003, the statue was blown up, knocking it off its base and causing it to fall into the bay, an act described as an \"act of vandalism\" without further details on the perpetrators or their motivations."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"The statue was doused in red paint in 2017 as part of a protest against whale hunting, a clear indication of a societal factor driving the vandalism."},{"citations":{"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":1.0},"text":"During worldwide protests after the death of George Floyd, the words \"racist fish\" were painted on the base of the statue in 2020, reflect