ay, in what police say is a \u201ccase of vandalism \u201d at Copenhagen \u2019 s most famous landmark and a popular tourist destination.\nAs specified, the front part of the stone on which the monument is erected is painted.\nAt the same time, the police still do not know \u201cwho is behind this incident. \u201d\n\"The answer is on the statue of an angel.\"\nThe most terrible secret of the Vatican is about to be revealed\nNews feed\n0\nNew firstOld firstFirst\nloader\nOn-line\nTitle of the material to be opened\nTo participate in the discussion,\nlog in or register\nloader\nChats\nTitle of the material to be opened","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2023-0006.json.gz:216847","uncompressed_offset":313497135,"url":"ria.ru/20230302/rusalochka-1855334372.html","warc_date":"2023-03-03T01:36:25.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:22783762-0562-4cf0-bd52-4a8a39cccb8e>","warc_url":"https://ria.ru/20230302/rusalochka-1855334372.html"},"created":"2023-03-03T01:59:46.000Z","lang":"eng"},"0bd19f72-d261-4b92-895b-6f6769aaf31f_360328435":{"id":"0bd19f72-d261-4b92-895b-6f6769aaf31f_360328435","text":"Danish police investigate who \u201cspoiled \u201d the famous monument to the Little Mermaid with the colors of the Russian flag\n03.03.2023, 7: 15, Misc\nSubscribe to Telegram channel\nSubscribe to Google News\nSupport at Patreon\nOn the pedestal of the famous statue of the Little Mermaid in Copenhagen, a Russian tricolor appeared, says The Guardian.\nThe Danish police have launched an investigation into such an \u201cact of vandalism \u201d, which is perceived as a sign of support in the Ukrainian conflict.\nAP\nIn Copenhagen, unknown people painted the foundation of the statue of the Mermaid in Copenhagen in the colors of the Russian flag, writes The Guardian.\nAccording to the publication, the tricolor appeared on Thursday night on the stone, which serves as a pedestal for the famous Danish monument.\nThe police in Copenhagen said that law enforcement officers visited the crime scene and registered an \u201cact of vandalism \u201d.\nThe police began an investigation and are trying to find \u201cevidence \u201d.\nThe actions of unknown persons are perceived as a sign of support for the Kremlin in the Ukrainian conflict.\nThe article notes that the statue of the Little Mermaid weighing 175 kg was created by sculptor Edward Eriksen, who was inspired by the main character of the fairy tale of the same name by Hans Christian Andersen.\nThe monument suffered from vandals many times: in 1964 her head was stolen, in 1984 her hand was cut off, in 1998 her head was stolen again, but later returned, and in 2003 the statue was blown up.\nIn addition, the Little Mermaid has been painted or signed many times.\nThe last time it happened in 2020, when it appeared the mysterious inscription \u201cRacist fish \u201d, writes The Guardian.\nView commentsNo comments\nPrivacy Policy - GDPR\nSite map \u2192\nFor information cooperation, advertising and publication of ads, write to the address: [email protected]\nSupport the project:\nUMoney- 410011013132383\nWebMoney \u2013 Z399334682366, E296477880853, X100503068090\n18 + \u00a9 2002-2022 RYBINSKonLine: All you wanted to know...","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2023-0006.json.gz:220977","uncompressed_offset":360328435,"url":"ryb.ru/2023/03/03/1947475","warc_date":"2023-03-03T04:24:23.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:0bd19f72-d261-4b92-895b-6f6769aaf31f>","warc_url":"https://ryb.ru/2023/03/03/1947475"},"created":"2023-03-03T04:52:52.000Z","lang":"eng"},"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400":{"id":"f535b8c5-32d1-4b5e-8c17-6635fe71fd07_946484400","text":"Russian Flag Painted on Copenhagen's Most Famous Landmark\n\nIt's the latest in a long line of attacks on Little Mermaid statue\nBy Rob Quinn, \u00a0Newser Staff\nPosted Mar 2, 2023 10:15 AM CST\n\nThe Little Mermaid statue in Copenhagen, one of Denmark's most famous landmarks, has been vandalized yet again, this time with the Russian flag. Authorities said Thursday that the white, blue, and red stripes of the Russian flag were painted on the stone the statue sits on, Reuters reports. Police said the vandalism was discovered early Thursday. \"We are of course launching an investigation to find out who did it and when and how it happened,\" a police spokesman said, per Jyllands-Posten.\n\nDenmark, like other European nations, has strongly criticized Russia's war against Ukraine. The small statue, a tribute to the Hans Christian Andersen fairy tale, sits off a waterfront promenade in the Danish capital. It has been vandalized many times since it was installed 110 years ago, AFP reports. It has been decapitated twice and was knocked off its base with explosives in 2003. In 2017, it was doused in red paint in a protest against whale hunting. In 2020, during worldwide protests after the death of George Floyd, the words \"racist fish\" were painted on the base, though Andersen scholars said they weren't aware of any racist elements in the fairy tale. (Read more The Little Mermaid stories.)\n\nWe use cookies. By Clicking \"OK\" or any content on this site, you agree to allow cookies to be placed. Read more in our privacy policy.\nGet the news faster.\nTap to install our app.\nX\nInstall the Newser News app\nin two easy steps:\n1. Tap in your navigation bar.\n2. Tap to Add to Home Screen.\n\nX","url":"https://www.newser.com/story/332238/little-mermaid-statue-vandalized-with-russian-flag.html"},"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268":{"id":"4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4_592630268","text":"Unknown people draw Russian flag on a statue of a mermaid in Copenhagen\nCOPENHAGEN (AFP) - The iconic Little Mermaid statue in the Danish capital Copenhagen was vandalized on Wednesday night as unidentified people painted the Russian flag on its base.\nAnnouncement\nAn AFP correspondent reported that the Russian flag was painted under unknown circumstances on the stone above which a statue of the Little Mermaid, inspired by the heroine of one of the stories of the writer Hans Christian Andersen, was installed.\nDanish police said they were launching an investigation into the incident, without giving any indication of the source of the move, which shows clear support for Russia amid the ongoing war in Ukraine.\nA Copenhagen police spokesman told AFP: \"We are investigating the area in order to find any evidence.\"\nA small number of tourists in the area took pictures of the statue in the port of Copenhagen, which was vandalized on Thursday morning.\nThe Little Mermaid statue on a largely unfrequented promenade has been targeted several times since it was installed in 1913.\nIn 1964, the head of the nymph was stolen for the first time without being recovered.\nIn 1998, a group of vandals cut off the head of the statue again, but it was later restored.\nThis monument was exposed to the explosion in 2003.\nThe statue, created by Danish sculptor Edvard Eriksen, has also been targeted several times with graffiti or graffiti, most recently in 2020 with the inscription \u201cracist fish \u201d.","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2023-0006.json.gz:38440","uncompressed_offset":592630268,"url":"www.france24.com/ar/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%85%D8%B1%D8%A9/20230302-%D9%85%D8%AC%D9%87%D9%88%D9%84%D9%88%D9%86-%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%85%D9%88%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B3%D9%8A-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%AA%D9%85%D8%AB%D8%A7%D9%84-%D8%AD%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%AD%D8%B1-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D9%83%D9%88%D8%A8%D9%86%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%BA%D9%86","warc_date":"2023-03-03T12:29:55.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:4d810b6c-4ef2-4afe-b264-6fb44830a9e4>","warc_url":"https://www.france24.com/ar/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%85%D8%B1%D8%A9/20230302-%D9%85%D8%AC%D9%87%D9%88%D9%84%D9%88%D9%86-%D9%