ities in Mexico.\nAccording to dozens of studies published in recent years, avocado cultivation also has negative effects on local communities. In some areas, demand for avocados has led to land grabbing, community displacement, labor exploitation, and avocado cultivation in the Mexican state of Michoac\u00e1n has led to the displacement of indigenous communities and the exploitation of often paid migrant workers. Some studies have shown that the expansion of avocado cultivation has displaced traditional crops, leading to food insecurity and loss of biodiversity.\nAccording to the study, governments around the world can take various measures to mitigate the impact of this agriculture on the climate, and one way is to promote sustainable avocado farming practices that reduce water use and reduce the use of chemicals. Protect the environment, provide financial incentives to farmers and enact laws that will deter illegal and criminal practices in these countries.","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2023-0012.json.gz:13665","uncompressed_offset":195587657,"url":"www.arab48.com/%D9%85%D8%AC%D9%84%D8%A9-%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A8-48/%D9%85%D8%AC%D9%84%D8%A9-%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A8-48/2023/04/24/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%81%D9%88%D9%83%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%88-%D9%85%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%A3%D8%AB%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D9%8A%D8%A6%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AA%D8%AD%D9%83%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B3%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%82-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%A9","warc_date":"2023-04-24T16:35:22.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:9f7babf6-335c-4686-b3fe-7602641d29a4>","warc_url":"https://www.arab48.com/%D9%85%D8%AC%D9%84%D8%A9-%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A8-48/%D9%85%D8%AC%D9%84%D8%A9-%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A8-48/2023/04/24/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%81%D9%88%D9%83%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%88-%D9%85%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%A3%D8%AB%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D9%8A%D8%A6%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AA%D8%AD%D9%83%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B3%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%82-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%A9"},"created":"2023-04-24T16:43:27.000Z","lang":"eng"},"c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865":{"id":"c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0_639626865","text":"\u2022 En\nDrug lord avocado rises in Mexico, superfood wreaks ecological havoc\n(Photo by Pixabay _ tookapic)\nAs a superfood, avocado has gained a lot of attention in recent years, and many cafes and restaurants have taken advantage of this trend, launching avocado meals and beverages. However, as the demand for avocado has increased, the cultivation of agricultural land has also expanded, which has caused ecological havoc in Mexico, the country of origin, and the rise of \"avocado criminal organizations.\"\nAvocado is native to Central America, Mexico and Peru, with Mexico \u2019 s largest producing region located in the southern state of Michoac\u00e1n, producing 70% of the country \u2019 s avocado, and the neighboring state of Jalisco, producing about 11% of the country \u2019 s avocado. As demand for avocado grows, the cultivation of avocado spreads to other states, including Colima. and Chiapas.\nHowever, this wave of expansion of the avocado garden has not been carefully evaluated, but under the guidance of local criminal organizations, with almost brutal methods of deforestation, the local preservation of the original forest has been completely destroyed.\nAccording to the conservation news website Mongabay, one tree in Jalisco is illegally cut down every 75 seconds to be converted into a casserole garden, with around 1,100 trees disappearing every day.\nThe study found that in 2010, Jalisco \u2019 s avocado garden was about 0.84 million hectares, but by 2021, it has reached 27.8 million hectares, more than tripled, and nearly half of the state \u2019 s 56,000 hectares of agricultural land has been used to grow avocado; and correspondingly, deforestation has accelerated since 2019, at least 0.51 million hectares of woodland has become avocado, resulting in pristine acorn. A large number of forests and evergreen forests have disappeared.\nUnder the avocado craze, criminal organizations also sniffed business opportunities, and the notorious Mexican drug lord Nemesio Oseguera Cervantes extended his reach into the field, and his Jalisco New Generation Cartel acquired the land of local residents and transplanted the avocado to obtain huge amounts. Profit.\nLocals point out that not only private land, but also protected woodlands that require official permission to convert to other crops, and that even if people report to the government that these organizations have substantial control over these areas, they end up sinking into the sea, with the result of course more virgin forest areas being destroyed.\nIn addition, compared to the original forest, planting avocado requires a lot of water, so after the new avocado garden is planted, it is necessary to build a large water storage tank to reserve irrigation water, which reduces the function of rainwater infiltration and local water collection.\nMexico is not a country with abundant water resources. As the number of avocado trees continues to increase, it will undoubtedly worsen the local water shortage and exacerbate political tensions.\nOn the other hand, there are also locals who try to coexist with the original ecology and introduce more eco-friendly avocados.\nJavier Maga\u00f1a C\u00e1rdenas, a avocado farmer who has long maintained the forest and helped restore the trees, said the authorities should establish a system to help identify and verify the provenance of avocados and ensure that illegal avocados are eliminated by consumers.\nAlready, many smallholder farmers have partnered with the Rainforest Alliance, a non-governmental organization, and around 1,500 hectares of avocado gardens in Jalisco have been certified for sustainable agriculture.\nSergio Graf Montero, head of the Jalisco Ministry of Environment and Territorial Development (SEMADET), said that as long as the demand for non-destructive avocados in the market rises, farmers will naturally choose such methods, and it is still consumers who determine the future of the ecology.\nUpdated: 2023-06-18 19: 38 GMT + 08: 00","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2023-0018.json.gz:4902","uncompressed_offset":639626865,"url":"www.taiwannews.com.tw/ch/news/4922215","warc_date":"2023-06-18T10:52:17.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:c4df1771-8297-4414-adac-d7cd6bb376e0>","warc_url":"https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/ch/news/4922215"},"created":"2023-06-18T11:38:47.000Z","lang":"eng"}}}
{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T146","run_id":"chili","topic_id":"1015","task":"multilingual","request_id":"1015","narrative_id":"1015"},"responses":[{"citations":{},"text":"<think>"},{"citations":{},"text":"</think>"},{"citations":{"6e47a5cf-47a7-42a3-812e-ef81ba1e7a5f_46222320":1.0},"text":"The Flat Earth Society operates in multiple countries, including Sweden, Canada, Australia, Brazil, France, Germany, the UK, Italy, Russia, Spain, and others. These organizations promote flat Earth theories through events, publications, and online communities."},{"citations":{"6e47a5cf-47a7-42a3-812e-ef81ba1e7a5f_46222320":1.0},"text":"The Flat Earth Society Australia was founded in 2013, while the Flat Earth Society Sweden publishes a magazine called *The Flat Earth News*."},{"citations":{"6e47a5cf-47a7-42a3-812e-ef81ba1e7a5f_46222320":1.0},"text":"Flat Earth believers often cite perceived flaws in mainstream science, such as questioning satellite imagery, GPS accuracy, and the curvature of the Earth. They argue that the Earth is a flat disk with the North Pole at the center, and that the Sun and Moon are celestial bodies that move in a dome-shaped sky."},{"citations":{"6e47a5cf-47a7-42a3-812e-ef81ba1e7a5f_46222320":1.0},"text":"The resurgence of flat Earth beliefs is linked to factors like distrust in institutions, the spread of misinformation online, and a desire for alternative explanations to complex scientific concepts. Many adherents are young adults who engage with conspiracy theories and online forums."},{"citations":{"6e47a5cf-47a7-42a3-812e-ef81ba1e7a5f_46222320":1.0},"text":"While some view flat Earth beliefs as harmless eccentricities, others warn that they can foster skepticism toward scientific consensus and critical thinking. Parents should consider discussing the importance of evidence-based reasoning with their children, especially if the friend\u2019s family promotes extreme or dangerous ideas."}],"answer":[{"citations":{},"text":"<think>"},{"citat