itives in salmon farming, though specific regulations may vary by country."},{"citations":{"09cbaa0c-5e42-4814-a1a1-3e28d939b1c4_429459585":1.0},"text":" These guidelines aim to ensure the safe and effective use of additives while maintaining the quality and safety of salmon for human consumption."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"09cbaa0c-5e42-4814-a1a1-3e28d939b1c4_429459585":1.0},"text":"Feed additives are used in salmon farming to enhance productivity and improve the properties of salmon."},{"citations":{"09cbaa0c-5e42-4814-a1a1-3e28d939b1c4_429459585":1.0},"text":" These additives include vitamins, amino acids, and mineral salts, which are essential for the growth and health of salmon."},{"citations":{"09cbaa0c-5e42-4814-a1a1-3e28d939b1c4_429459585":1.0},"text":"Vitamins, such as fat-soluble and water-soluble vitamins, play an active role in the digestion process and contribute to improving immunity in salmon."},{"citations":{"09cbaa0c-5e42-4814-a1a1-3e28d939b1c4_429459585":1.0},"text":" Amino acids, like lysine and methionine, are crucial for protein synthesis and immune function, supporting the structural and functional needs of salmon."},{"citations":{"09cbaa0c-5e42-4814-a1a1-3e28d939b1c4_429459585":1.0},"text":"Mineral salts, including calcium, potassium, magnesium, and sodium, are vital for bone formation, electrolyte balance, and physiological processes in salmon."},{"citations":{"09cbaa0c-5e42-4814-a1a1-3e28d939b1c4_429459585":1.0},"text":" These additives ensure the nutritional requirements of salmon are met, leading to optimized growth and health."},{"citations":{"09cbaa0c-5e42-4814-a1a1-3e28d939b1c4_429459585":1.0},"text":"The use of feed additives can increase productivity and immunity rates in salmon, resulting in economic savings for farmers and improved profitability."},{"citations":{"09cbaa0c-5e42-4814-a1a1-3e28d939b1c4_429459585":1.0},"text":" This also enhances the quality and safety of salmon for human consumption by ensuring optimal health and redu