ic activity, where he touched on the file of feed additives, explaining its importance to the poultry production industry, which is mainly based on maximizing the benefit of all inputs.\nThe report stressed that the desired goal of the use of feed additives, is to achieve the maximum possible absorption rate of protein, carbohydrates and fats, from the feed formula provided to birds, in a way that enhances the doubling of their productivity and improve their properties.\nFeed additives are divided into two main sections: Feed additives: are those additives that enter the food directly, most notably vitamins of both types \u201cfat \u201d and\u201c soluble in water \u201d, and play an active role in the completion of the process of digestion, in addition to its strong contribution to improving immunity.\nThe report added that the breeder aims to maximize productivity and double immunity rates, which achieves a tangible economic savings for the breeder, and is reflected positively on the level of profitability expected by the end of each cycle, explaining that amino acids \u201camino acid \u201d: the cell building unit and the pillar of animal protein production, in addition to its important role in the formation of immune bodies.\nThe report added that the mineral salts: divided into two basic \u201cstructural salts \u201d, the most important of which are\u201c calcium, potassium, magnesium \u201d, which enter as the main part in the synthesis of bones, and \u201cnon-food salts \u201d, and play the role of regulator of metabolic processes that take place within the body.\nThe report pointed out that there are non-food feed additives: the latest trend in the world of feed additives, which specialists call \u201cyeasts \u201d or\u201c plastics, \u201d and represent a type of bacteria beneficial to living organisms.\nThe report stressed that the latest scientific research revealed that each gram of intestinal juice of a healthy human or animal, contains \"1210\" bacterial organism, as one of the most prominent manifestations of health, while some studies have found that 30% of the weight of the organism is only bacteria.","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2023-0016.json.gz:7725","uncompressed_offset":429459585,"url":"www.dostor.org/4409745","warc_date":"2023-05-30T06:49:37.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:09cbaa0c-5e42-4814-a1a1-3e28d939b1c4>","warc_url":"https://www.dostor.org/4409745"},"created":"2023-05-30T07:20:04.000Z","lang":"eng"}}}
