 flat Earth theories."},{"citations":{"6e47a5cf-47a7-42a3-812e-ef81ba1e7a5f_46222320":1.0},"text":"Th"}],"references":["6e47a5cf-47a7-42a3-812e-ef81ba1e7a5f_46222320","f61994b0-dc34-40d6-a1e2-a7f66b22774b_548175167"],"documents":{"f61994b0-dc34-40d6-a1e2-a7f66b22774b_548175167":{"id":"f61994b0-dc34-40d6-a1e2-a7f66b22774b_548175167","text":"How did Muslim scholars refute the flat Earth theory a thousand years ago?\nThe flat earth is currently one of the most famous scientific myths widespread in the Arab world, and has private groups on social media met by supporters from all over, and in recent days has been controversial because of statements by the Egyptian artist Mohamed Sobhy.\nThere are two histories to this theory, not one; the first is ancient and the second is modern.\nA number of Greek philosophers believed that the earth was flat, and the ancient Scandinavian and German peoples also believed that the earth was flat and surrounded by oceans, and the common belief in ancient China was that the earth was square and flat while the sky was spherical.\nBut it \u2019 s really surprising to know that early astronomers assumed its sphericity, and they were from almost every culture: Pythagoras, who lived about 2,500 years ago, proposed the sphericity of the Earth based on his observations of the moon during the eclipse.\nPythagorean's observations are still evidence of a refutation of the flat Earth theory: Pythagorean observed that the shadow that the Earth casts on the Moon during the eclipse is always round.\nRegardless of the moon-facing part of the planet, eclipses occur everywhere in the world.\nThe idea of a lunar eclipse is simple: put a big lamp in the middle of your room and turn off the rest of the lights, stand at a distance of one meter from it, now turn around while you reach your hands in front of you with a tennis ball, when you give your back to the lamp and pass the tennis ball in the shadow extended in front of you because of your body, this is the eclipse.\nTo Eratosthenes\nEratosthenes, born 276 BC, was the first to measure the circumference of the Earth using a simple method involving the angle of the Sun at different locations.\nEratosthenes was astonished to read that the columns in the ancient Egyptian temples of Aswan on the afternoon of June 21 of each year did not leave a shadow under them, and the mystery of the wonder was that the columns in Alexandria left a shadow under them on the afternoon of the same day.\nEratosthenes came to the conclusion that the earth must be convex and not flat, otherwise the columns in Alexandria would appear shadowless, and then after reflection Eratosthenes came to the clever idea that we could measure the length of the shadow in Aswan which is zero, and its length in Alexandria, and then measure the distance between Alexandria and Aswan, and infer the circumference of the earth.\nThe story goes that he sent a man to measure the distance, so that with some simple geometry he could measure the circumference of the Earth, which he concluded was about 39,348 kilometers.\nEratosthenes' account was transferred to the Arabs from among the sciences they translated.\nAccording to Carlo Nelino in his book \"Astronomy: A History of the Arabs in the Middle Ages\", the Caliph al-Ma'mun al-Abbasi (who ruled from 813 to 833 AD) asked two teams of astronomers to test these calculations and come up with the most accurate measurement of the Earth's circumference....\nThe safe astronomer.\nThe method adopted by the Arabs is to go out into a perfectly flat desert, and then rely on the inclination of the polar star in the sky.\nThe ancients realized that the position of stars in the sky is affected by your place on Earth, the further you travel south, the lower the polar star in the sky until it disappears completely after the equator, and the more you travel north, the higher the polar star sky until it became above your head in the North Pole, which means that the Earth is round, otherwise the position of stars in the sky changes with your place on it.\nThe height of the polar star (and all other stars) is measured in degrees, and it is like to put a protractor in front of your eyes, the horizon is at zero, and then look at the protractor from the side to find at what degree the polar star stands, and this is something you can do exactly as the ancients did, and now astronomical software is easily available.\nAl-Ma'mun astronomers measured the height of the polar star, then moved north once and south once, until the amount of inclination of the polar star changes by one degree, and then measured the distance north and south, and this measured distance is one degree from the circumference of the Earth's circle, and it can know the rest of the circumference of the Earth, because the Earth is a ball, and like any ball, rotation around it requires 360 degrees.\nThe first team of Al-Ma \u2019 mun astronomers went out to the Sinjar desert, a small city in northwestern Iraq today, and the second team to the Palmyra desert in eastern Syria, and carried out the same experiments in both places. In the Sinjar desert, for example, the height of the polar star was about 35 degrees. south of the wedge site until the measurement dropped by a degree.\nAccording to al-Ma \u2019 mun \u2019 s astronomers, the scale of one degree was about 56 parsecs and two-thirds parsecs, which Nalino calculated \u2014 according to Edward Kennedy of the American University of Beirut in a paper published in the Encyclopedia of the History of Arab Sciences \u2014 to be 111.8 kilometers, a value used by later researchers such as al-Biruni and al-Toussi.\nCalculating the circumference of the Earth in this experiment, it turned out to be about 410,248 km, which was close to modern measurements (40075 km) in the most accurate way at the time.\nNote that the difference between the two measurements is about 1,100 years, and the reason for the difference is not related to the same method but to the ellipse of the Earth, as the distance between the two latitudes increases slightly as we head north.\nAbu Rayhan Al-Biruni\nThe second attempt was by Abu Rayhan al-Biruni, born in September 973 AD, who used the best and easiest formula to calculate the circumference of the Earth in his time.\nThe Al-Biruni method is based on triangulation, where the sunset is observed from the top of a high mountain overlooking flat ground to the horizon, the astrolabe measures the angle the sun descends relative to the observer on the top of the mountain, where the line connecting the observer on the top of the mountain and the horizon makes the sunset clock touch the planet Earth.\nIt is known that the tangent of a circle perpendicular to its diameter, and then we have a right-angled triangle at the horizon, and we can measure the radius of the Earth by knowing the height of the mountain, which is mathematically easy.\nCurrently, the same calculations can be applied by high school students, for example, in all countries of the Arab world, who have a good amount of trigonometry study.\nIn a study published in the International Journal of Sciences, an Italian team repeated al-Biruni \u2019 s experiment and concluded that its results for the radius of the Earth are equal to 3,928.77 English miles, which compares favorably, being 2% different, with the average reference radius at the measurement latitude, which is 3,847.80 miles.\nPakistani physicist Mazhar Mahmood Qureshi, in his book An Introduction to Muslim Contributions to Science and Technology, points out that al-Biruni \u2019 s experience in what is now Nandana Fort in the mountains of northern Pakistan is a typical example of the use of experimental scientific methods.\nThe most important book of al-Biruni astronomical is \"The Law of Masoudi\", in which al-Biruni collected all the astronomical problems of his time, and the way of al-Biruni was to present the origins of the matter and the views of the Indian, Greek and Arab astronomers and then weighted between them.\nModern history of flat earth\nBut at that point, you might ask yourself: if the sphericity of the Earth was obvious to Muslim scholars and their comrades in other parts of the world in ancient times, why did it come back?\nIn 1849, the English writer Samuel Rowbotham published a pamphlet entitled \"Oil Astronomy\" (from the Greek letter zeta, not oil), in which he defended the theory of the flat earth, and followed this with another entitled \"The Instability of Modern Astronomy and its opposition to the Bible\".\nIn 1883, Rowbotham founded oil societies in England and New York, shipping thousands of copies of his books to talk about flat earth.\nMeanwhile, William Carpenter, a printer and native of Greenwich, England, supported Rowbotham and advocated his theory, learning it from John Jasper and preaching to more people than any cleric of his generation in the southern United States. Once.\nFrom here the myth began to branch again in the United States, and then to Europe, and then to the Arab world and the rest of the world, but in this context it was mixed with conspiracy theories concerning secret groups trying to control the world by deluding people that the earth is round.\nThe proof of the sphericity of the earth is not new, and has a long history in which Muslim scholars have made an influential contribution, but because the \u201cflat earth \u201d has been transformed from ignorance of the nature of science into a conspiracy theory it has been imported along with other famous theories into our Arab world.\nSource: Al Jazeera + Websites","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2024-0019.json.gz:4960","uncompressed_offset":548175167,"url":"www.aljazeera.net/science/2024/7/24/%D9%83%D9%8A%D9%81-%D9%81%D9%86%D8%AF-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%A1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B3%D9%84%D9%85%D9%8A%D9%86-%D9%86%D8%B8%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%B6","warc_date":"2024-07-24T09:32:29.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:f61994b0-dc34-40d6-a1e2-a7f66b22774b>","warc_url":"https://www.aljazeera.net/science/2024/7/24/%D9%83%D9%8A%D9%81-%D9%81%D9%86%D8%AF-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%A1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B3%D9%84%D9%85%D9%8A%D9%86-%D9%86%D8%B8%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B1%D8%B6?traffic_source=rss"},"created":"2024-07-24T10:07:49.000Z","lang":"eng"},"6e47a5cf-47a7-42a3-812e-ef81ba1e7a5f_46222320":{"id":"6e47a5cf-47a7-42a3-812e-ef81ba1e7a5f_46222320","text":"\"The Lost Earth Truth 1\": The level of the earth seems to be the \"gold rush\" of our time.\nPhoto Credit: iStock\nWhat we want you to know is\nThrough the multi-dimensional advanced high-tech \"heterogeneous meta-helmet\", scientists learned that the earth is full of four-dimensional entrances, the third dimension of the material plane and the fourth dimension of the etheric plane are originally \"twins\".\nWritten by Radu Cinama\nTiping said it was the \"gold rush\" of this era.\nBased on a reference to the House of the Cabal, which hides the door to multidimensional interaction, I found an informative note that I had never seen before, floating among dozens of notes on my desk.\nIn general, I prefer to work in electronic form or wait for notes or files in digital format, but given my particular interest in the Dimension Portal, I decided to check everything on my desk, including the latest events.\nI do not know the reasons and methods, but the information I found was ignored.\nAfter reviewing notes and data summaries, I discovered an event called \u201cGround Floor \u2013 References \u201d, a\u201c movement \u201d that I \u2019 ve heard has made waves among people, but I never thought it would become a theme for our department.\nThe illusion of this idea is obvious, especially for those who have good judgment and personal experience of our planet from the perspective of outer space.\nI was a bit confused and didn \u2019 t know if I should read a few pages of summaries about the ground floor.\nI went to Lieutenant Nikola and asked him about it.\nHe told me that the information came from the operations department of another SRI division, an acronym for the Romanian Intelligence Agency, which has the status of a second level notice.\nThe lieutenant made it clear that the only reason this information reached our department was because it triggered an abnormal \"phenomenon\" in the world, but in our country, the number of \"followers\" is relatively small and the proportion is reasonable, and the level seems to be the \"gold rush\" of our time. It makes you speechless, even in a state of \u201cshock. \u201d\nI can understand that the paranoia and other obscure interests of hundreds of years ago amplify the lack of knowledge, which may occupy the minds of a relatively small number of people, but it is unreasonable to allow it to develop to the level of the international movement of the 21st century.\nFrom a heavenly point of view, I wonder if human stupidity can rise above that level, but I don \u2019 t quite believe in that prospect.\nHowever, even the most bizarre phenomena must be taken into account, at least taking into account the crowd and their opinions, which is one of the Secret Service's tasks.\nI did read the summary, which revealed the main points of the problem very clearly, but did not give any conclusions.\nSevere retrogression into the Middle Ages\nOn the same night, I took advantage of Cesar \u2019 s free time and shared the ground level problem with him, more as a social case than a research direction.\nCesar laughed loudly, talked about the topic for a while, and then suddenly turned to some very interesting questions.\nHe told me that three or four years ago, the issue was introduced to him and discussed with other colleagues in the intelligence department because there were signs that the idea was trending toward a consensus.\nOut of respect for readers, I don \u2019 t usually include such a discussion in my series.\nIt requires only a little wisdom and minimal scientific training to understand, and arguments in support of this theory are tantamount to ignorance and fanaticism.\nBeyond this, however, Cesar reveals some psychological cues that seem to be of some importance to general knowledge and social experience.\nWhen discussing topping with Cesar, the first point involves a large number of followers.\n\u201cThe mechanism for this strange theory of increased follower numbers is related to human isolation, \u201d says Cesar.\n\u201cIt \u2019 s as if the population is divided into two distinct categories, but this separation is actually based on each person \u2019 s level of consciousness, which is directly related to their vibration frequency. \u201d\n\u201cBut, \u201d I replied,\u201c I don \u2019 t know what caused this outbreak, and more and more people are insisting on these \u2018 arguments \u2019 without meaning. \u201d\nIt's more like a stupid virus. \"\n\u201cThis major shift in thinking patterns is not at the same wavelength as what is commonly understood in the world today.\nIn other words, such new ideas have nothing to do with the knowledge of our time.\nThis is an effective method, because the earth is flat, and the idea is strongly supported by mystical factors, as well as by those who are keen to see things stagnant and not progressing.\nThis is the best way to control it: take people away from reality, let them dream nonsense, support their fantasies, and encourage them to project.\nTherefore, it is controlled by imposing on the masses what they want.\nFollowers of earth thought, firmly believing in it, will seek to meet others, gather, and even separate themselves from others, because they will see others as fools deceived by lies.\nIn other words, they will be convinced that they are the ones who \u201cdiscovered \u201d the truth. While it is sad to hear the news, unfortunately, the situation is quite real. \u201d\n\u201cAlthough I have this report under my nose, I can \u2019 t believe it has reached this point.\nI feel like this is an ugly dream, as if some people in the world have voluntarily gone back hundreds of years.\nThat's how I feel.\nIncredibly, people \u2019 s minds today are still influenced by delusions that defy not only decent intelligence but also scientific reasoning, making everything frenzied.\nLook at the results! \u201d\nI showed Cesar \u2019 s estimated numbers and charts.\n\"I know.\nWe've talked to other colleagues, \"he said.\n\u201cYour surprise is evidenced by the huge difference in conceptualization and vibration frequency that people are beginning to feel.\nThis is a reality that has become increasingly prominent over time and cannot be ignored.\nThis is part of the isolation I told you about.\nIn principle, people interact with those who are evolving and those who prefer to stay in purely physical, crude or involuntary groups.\nThose in the first category perfect themselves, recognize the changes that are taking place on Earth, and experience certain emotional states and specific sensations.\nThat \u2019 s why it \u2019 s incredible for some people to think about problems in a medieval way, such as followers of the Earth Theory. \u201d\nCesar saw the astonishment on my face and hurried to prove what he said again.\n\u201cYes, I \u2019 m not exaggerating.\nThis is a return to the Middle Ages, because these people cannot evolve; instead, they return to a more archaic state of consciousness, closer to their true level of consciousness. \u201d\n\u201cWhy can \u2019 t they evolve? \u201d I asked in surprise.\nOf course, I know the answer, but it \u2019 s always a pleasure to capture Cesar \u2019 s explanation.\nIn addition, there is always a new element that can enrich my knowledge.\n\u201cBecause the current state of things they attract has nothing to do with the higher vibrations of the Earth, this feature is becoming more and more apparent. \u201d\n\u201cFor the followers of the Earth Plane, their consolation lies in the frenzy of these primitive ideas, which are maintained as free spirits and ideas are blocked.\nThe same was true during the Inquisition: a set of foolish and erroneous ideas was raised into law, and any violation of those ideas was enforced. \u201d\nWhen I think about it all, I hope I \u2019 m wrong.\n\u201cAre we back in the Middle Ages? History has set off a wave of extreme ideas.\nAncient people already knew that the earth was round, but the situation deteriorated in the Middle Ages, when there was a revival of modern science, but was this only to take us back to the Middle Ages now? \u201d (The author undoubtedly refers to the knowledge shared by Pythagoras and Aristotle, who both asserted that the earth is round, and the argument made by Eratonius in ancient Alexandria.)\nCesar calmly replied, \u201cWe don \u2019 t; but for the part that has degraded, yes. \u201d\nSeveral factors contributed to this.\nFollowers of the Earth \u2019 s theory are indignant at their opinionated views, their refusal to think logically or rationally on the basis of real arguments and evidence, their denial of evidence, and their deceitful defense of their position.\nIn general, this is a kind of missionary covering up fanaticism.\nThe psychological factor of the earth level, the mind pulls people's distance\nWe note that whenever fanaticism prevails, society is confronted with a lack of insight and the limitations of personal freedom.\nCesar gave me an example that better explains how this dilemma can be achieved in the context of a relatively developed civilization.\n\"This phenomenon is the same as in quantum physics.\nIf there is enough energy, the electrons can jump into higher orbits.\nIf there is not enough energy, it can be kept at a slightly higher level and relatively stable; but at some point, the remaining energy will be released in the form of photons, and the electron will return to the orbit where it was originally found, back to where it started.\nIn quantum physics, this is the basic orbit of electrons.\nIn other words, electrons with these characteristics will return to the level where they have a safe orbit. \u201d I interjected, clinging to the subject.\n\u201cI know that throughout human history, the idea that the earth is flat has long existed in some religions.\nModern astronomy has developed extensively since then.\nUranus, Neptune, and Pluto have only been discovered for about two hundred years.\nIn this sense, the ground floor is actually not very old, its memory is still fresh.\nPerhaps that is why some humans return to the state they once knew. \"\n\u201cThis is another factor, \u201d Cesar acknowledged,\u201c in any case, human society is changing from \u2018 possessiveness \u2019 to \u2018 feeling \u2019, that sense of possession, egoism, competition, and violence tends to be gradually replaced by pure and positive emotions and feelings, which are fundamental to love, altruism, and compassion. \u201d\nI have some doubts.\n\u201cIt \u2019 s hard to believe, because almost all of us are seeing the spread of these negative manifestations. \u201d\n\u201cAt first glance, it might be so.\nRemember, however, that most people on Earth are uneducated, and they \u2018 resort \u2019 to this illusion of competition, money, commerce, and lack of spirituality.\nA large number of people who are addicted to this dream, tend to oppose those who are guided only by spiritual values and seek a pure life with a clear meaning, and have achieved a balance at this point.\nThis is what we call isolation. \"\nIn fact, what Cesar wanted to say is that everyone is invited to participate in the great spiritual transformation of humanity and our planet, with the desire and dignity to demand that his life be the germ of light, spirituality and hope that we can enter a bright future.\nThis is an excellent ideal, but so far too few people have followed this ideal.\nBook Introduction\nThis excerpt is from The Lost Earth Truth 1: The Hidden History of Holographic Time Travel, published by Daxi Culture.\nWritten by Radu Cinamar\nTranslated by: Sandra\n\u2022 momo online bookstore\n\u2022 Enter TNL83 at Pubu E-Bookstore checkout to enjoy 83% off sitewide (excluding some items, such as physical, adult and designated items, cannot be combined with other offers)\n\u2022 If you purchase the book through the links above, Key Review Network will receive a score profit from it.\nRadu Cinamar became famous after revealing an unprecedented and mysterious collaboration between the US and Romanian militaries.\nAmerican and Romanian troops have made an expedition under the Romanian Sphinx in the Bucegi Mountains and discovered the greatest archaeological discovery of all time: a mysterious chamber about 50,000 years old, containing a holographic record of human history of the Earth, biological resonance imaging technology, and three mysterious tunnels that lead to secrets deep in the heart of the earth.\nDespite the political intrigue, confusion, and restrictions surrounding this great discovery, the expedition leader allowed Radu Sinamar to visit and explore the artifacts.\nSince then, Radu \u2019 s life has been a labyrinthine adventure, filled with strange events, secret connections, and unusual people and things.\nThis book delves into ancient history in an unprecedented way, through the interaction of advanced technology \u2019 s \u201cheterogeneous helmets \u201d with the author \u2019 s cerebral cortex and intuition, presenting more than 70 stunning images of the scene, the result of which is holographic projection, explaining and illustrating the DNA changes that took place over thousands of years and how humans evolved into what they are today.\nReveals the mystery of how multiple alien civilizations influenced and guided human DNA to evolve to a higher level.\nSome of the hot spots in human history, which in the past either remained unknown or were only considered from a mythological point of view, include: Atlantis, Troy, Shambhala, and Huppelburia.\nDisrupting the myths of the past, this book provides rich and accurate communications from the actual scene of holographic technology, combining esoteric knowledge and some scientific factors.\nSpecial emphasis is placed on the \"intersection\" between the physical dimension and the etheric dimension and on the cracks or entrances between the dimensions.\nIn addition to revealing the ancient history of mankind, this fascinating work also describes a time out to see the origins of humanity and its hope for the future.\nBook Features\nTime-lapse decoding! The beginning of important human change\nThrough the multi-dimensional advanced high-tech \"heterogeneous meta-helmet\", scientists learned that the earth is full of four-dimensional entrances, the third dimension of the material plane and the fourth dimension of the etheric plane are originally \"twins\".\nAnd you can see the \"cosmic record\" in the holographic image!\nYou can also overlook the cross-section of the earth, covering the deep human genetic technology and high-dimensional cosmic civilization, and no book in its amazing history has been exposed so far!\nEditor-in-Chief: Weng Shihang\nEditor-in-chief: Bohan Pan\nTags:","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2021-0032.json.gz:7860","uncompressed_offset":46222320,"url":"www.thenewslens.com/article/158283","warc_date":"2021-11-05T12:40:52.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:6e47a5cf-47a7-42a3-812e-ef81ba1e7a5f>","warc_url":"https://www.thenewslens.com/article/158283?utm_source=feedburner&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=Feed%3A+TheNewsLens+%28The+News+Lens+%E9%97%9C%E9%8D%B5%E8%A9%95%E8%AB%96%E7%B6%B2%29"},"created":"2021-11-05T12:43:20.000Z","lang":"eng"}}}
{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T146","run_id":"chili","topic_id":"1062","task":"multilingual","request_id":"1062","narrative_id":"1062"},"responses":[{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":1.0},"text":"The Middle East is traditionally known for oil wealth, but several countries have begun investing heavily in solar energy as part of their energy transition strategies."},{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":1.0},"text":"The UAE is a leader in solar energy projects, with the Mohammed bin Rashid Al Maktoum Solar Park being the world\u2019s largest IPP solar site."},{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":1.0},"text":"The Al Dhafra Solar PV Plant is being built as the world\u2019s largest solar power plant with a capacity of 2 GW."},{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":1.0},"text":"Masdar City is the most sustainable urban community in the world."},{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":1.0},"text":"The UAE\u2019s Advanced Finance Development Fund (ADFD) is committed to funding innovative projects to accelerate access to sustainable energy."},{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":1.0},"text":"The Middle East and North Africa (MENA) region has high solar energy potential, with countries like Saudi Arabia, the United Arab Emirates, Morocco, and Egypt contributing on average annual solar radiation exceeding 2,000 kWh/m\u00b2."},{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":1.0},"text":"Solar energy is crucial for meeting future energy needs amid population and economic growth, as well as concerns about climate change and environmental sustainability."},{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":1.0},"text":"The Middle East\u2019s solar energy initiatives are strengthening their role in supporting international efforts to address climate change."},{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-