 transition."},{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":1.0},"text":"The Arab Economic and Social Development Summit adopted a renewable energy initiative to increase capacity from 12 GW in 2013 to 80 GW by 2030."},{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":1.0},"text":"The Benban Solar Park in Egypt has a 1,800 MW capacity, and the Gulf of Suez Wind Power Project is a 1,100 MW wind project."},{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":1.0},"text":"The document also mentions the importance of regulatory reforms and the need for a supportive policy environment to achieve these goals."},{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":1.0},"text":"The Middle East's high dust density, which affects solar energy productivity, is a key challenge for solar energy projects in the region."},{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":1.0},"text":"The International Solar Alliance's role in reducing the cost of solar energy is significant, as the Middle East has significant solar energy potential, but high temperatures affect solar panel efficiency."},{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":1.0},"text":"The region's investment in solar energy projects reflects a commitment to reducing carbon dioxide emissions and achieving climate goals."},{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":1.0},"text":"The UAE's commitment to funding innovative projects to accelerate access to sustainable energy is crucial, as the UAE's energy transition strategies aim to reduce reliance on fossil fuels and lower carbon emissions."},{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":1.0},"text":"The UAE's ADFD funding partnerships with IRENA and the World Future Energy Summit's release of the Solar Outlook 2024 report indicate that governments are providing support and creating partnerships to scale up solar energy development."},{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":1.0},"text":"The role of international agreements and initiatives, such as the Paris Climate Agreement, is significant, as countries like Egypt and Saudi Arabia are part of these agreements, showing their global commitment to renewable energy and climate goals."},{"citations":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":1.0},"text":"The economic impact of solar energy projects, such as the UAE's investment in the power sector and expected job creation, is substantial, as the document on Egypt's project states that it will drive local economic growth, including the power sector."}],"references":["3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401"],"documents":{"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401":{"id":"3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47_782728401","text":"In numbers...\nArab countries race to double their renewable energy production by 2030\nECONOMY\nPublish\n3 minutes read\nDUBAI, United Arab Emirates \u2014 (CNN) Arab countries are on track to grow their utility-scale wind and solar capacity by more than 500% by 2023, according to a report by Global Energy Monitor.\nAccording to the report, the Middle East and North Africa (MENA) region has enormous potential for large-scale wind and solar power projects because of its favorable climate and sunny weather for most of the year.\nArab countries are planning more than 73 gigawatts of utility-scale solar and wind projects, a more than fivefold increase in current capacity, which together with operational projects will account for 91% of the Arab League \u2019 s renewable energy goals for 2030.\nThe UAE is at the top of the list of Arab countries that produce the most electricity from solar energy, with solar plants producing 2.6 gigawatts of electricity.\nEgypt is among the Arab countries that produce the most electricity from wind power at 1.6 gigawatts.\nEgypt produces 1.9 gigawatts of electricity from solar power plants.\nEgypt \u2019 s total electricity production from both places it at the top of the list of Arab countries with a production capacity of 3.5 gigawatts.\nThanks to its huge investments in solar electricity production, the UAE ranks second in wind and solar electricity production, followed by Morocco in third place with 1.9 GW and Jordan in fourth place with 1.7 GW.\nWhile Egypt, the United Arab Emirates, Morocco and Jordan are the first Arab countries to initiate wind and solar power plants, Oman, Algeria and Kuwait are poised to follow suit, ranking first in expected solar and wind power production in the near future.\nHere are the top Arab countries in terms of the current operation of solar and wind energy on the scale of utilities and the capacity of wind and solar energy expected to be produced at the level of each country in the Arab region.","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2022-0033.json.gz:8002","uncompressed_offset":782728401,"url":"arabic.cnn.com/business/article/2022/11/06/renewable-energy-capacity-arab-region-infographic","warc_date":"2022-11-06T11:53:59.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:3b3f30e3-8208-46d0-b297-b7d98c560b47>","warc_url":"https://arabic.cnn.com/business/article/2022/11/06/renewable-energy-capacity-arab-region-infographic"},"created":"2022-11-06T12:59:20.000Z","lang":"eng"}}}
{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T146","run_id":"chili","topic_id":"1063","task":"multilingual","request_id":"1063","narrative_id":"1063"},"responses":[{"citations":{"815e093a-531c-4359-b12e-6e824a4bcb86_683341332":1.0},"text":"Renewable energy transition in the Middle East aims to achieve economic diversification and reduce dependence on oil and related industries."},{"citations":{"815e093a-531c-4359-b12e-6e824a4bcb86_683341332":1.0},"text":"The Middle East countries hope to turn their surplus renewable energy into new, dependable foreign revenues through innovative technologies."},{"citations":{"815e093a-531c-4359-b12e-6e824a4bcb86_683341332":1.0},"text":"Renewable energy development can stimulate local economies and create new dependent income sources."},{"citations":{"815e093a-531c-4359-b12e-6e824a4bcb86_683341332":1.0},"text":"Jordan successfully achieved its national roadmap, with renewable energy accounting for 31% of total energy, and plans to increase this target to 50%."},{"citations":{"e97df0fb-7f68-4a7a-8b3c-c9b151cb58ac_1057855493":1.0},"text":"The renewable energy sector is a significant driver of economic growth and job creation, with the potential to create millions more jobs as the industry expands."},{"citations":{"e97df0fb-7f68-4a7a-8b3c-c9b151cb58ac_1057855493":1.0},"text":"Renewable energy projects can spur economic development in rural and underdeveloped areas by providing new infrastructure and investment opportunities."},{"citations":{"815e093a-531c-4359-b12e-6e824a4bcb86_683341332":1.0},"text":"The Middle East countries face challenges in the transition to renewable energy, including the need for foreign technology and talent, but also see it as a valuable development opportunity."},{"citations":{"815e093a-531c-4359-b12e-6e824a4bcb86_683341332":1.0},"text":"Jordan has a wealth of renewable energy resources, including solar, wind, geothermal, and bioenergy, and has state-of-the-art renewable energy laws and regulatory mechanisms."},{