, movie dubbing, game characters, virtual assistants, and chatbots."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"However, misuse risks include scams, fake multilingual voices, and unauthorized audio creation."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"A 2023 incident involved ElevenLabs\u2019 software generating a realistic Emma Watson voice, sparking viral attention."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"Legitimate uses include Paradox Interactive\u2019s enhanced audio content for games."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"OpenAI has phased out voice recognition for bank verification and developed content tracking technologies."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"Legal and ethical concerns involve privacy, intellectual property, and abuse potential."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"A 2023 scam case demonstrated cloned voices being used to extort money from loved ones."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"Regulatory debates highlight the need for guidelines to address misuse and societal impact."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"Companies like ElevenLabs and OpenAI emphasize security and transparency in their practices."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"The technology\u2019s ability to create realistic audio aids language learning but raises ethical issues like consent violations."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"Balancing innovation with responsibility is critical to managing its dual potential for benefit and harm."}],"references":["20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971"],"documents":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":{"id":"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971","text":"General Supervision\nElham Aboul Fath\nEditor-in-Chief\nThank you for your patience.\nGeneral Supervision\nElham Aboul Fath\nEditor-in-Chief\nThank you for your patience.\nA new invention in artificial intelligence imitates sounds\nSome of the biggest players in AI are seeking to stay ahead of the competition by launching their own gadgets, with Meta recently introducing Voicebox, an artificial speech generator integrated with artificial intelligence and based on texts.\nThe company believes that thanks to this technology, it has surpassed all current models in the field.\nAnd while the system isn \u2019 t widely available for public use yet, Meta has made demos available to anyone interested in learning more about Voicebox.\nThe system can be used to edit acoustics through a natural sound generator, and can intelligently edit noise in audio files and reproduce sound accurately.\nVoicebox is able to match the style of voice input and generate audio text clips, allowing blind users to provide the system with an audio clip of one of their friends so Voicebox can read their messages written in their friend \u2019 s voice using artificial intelligence.\nThe system can solve tasks through contextual learning, so that it can process texts that have not been given before and generate context and changes in the same way that people read by relying on previous knowledge to learn and face new challenges.\nThe ethical and legal implications of this new tool cannot be ignored, as anyone can produce audio clips using someone \u2019 s audio recordings and claiming to speak anything they want, without permission.\nThe company claims in its paper that the binary classification model can distinguish between real speech and that it was created by Voicebox.\nVoicebox trains over 60,000 hours of English audiobooks and 50,000 hours of multilingual audiobooks in six different languages.\nThe system can also convert written text into spoken speech in one or several languages without having to be specially trained for each language.\nMeta claims that Voicebox can produce various audio clips 20 times faster than Microsoft \u2019 s Val-E and with better quality.\nIn addition to high speed and accuracy, Voicebox can generate audio clips in different languages without having to be specially trained for each language.","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2023-0018.json.gz:60529","uncompressed_offset":636246971,"url":"www.elbalad.news/5823648","warc_date":"2023-06-26T11:15:49.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5>","warc_url":"https://www.elbalad.news/5823648"},"created":"2023-06-26T11:45:52.000Z","lang":"eng"}}}
{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T146","run_id":"chili","topic_id":"1076","task":"multilingual","request_id":"1076","narrative_id":"1076"},"responses":[{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"Voice cloning technology has developed significantly, becoming increasingly realistic and accessible, raising both excitement and concern."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"It uses machine learning algorithms to simulate anyone\u2019s voice, requiring specific voice data to analyze and learn the unique patterns of an individual."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"Voice cloning tools are now available on the internet, allowing anyone to use them with no technical knowledge or cost."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"ElevenLabs, a company developing speech cloning technology, offers a free and premium service to generate audio content for users."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"The technology has applications in industries such as audiobooks, movie dubbing, game characters, and promotions, as well as in virtual assistants and chatbots."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"OpenAI, a company focused on AI research, has developed a text-to-speech tool that can generate natural-sounding human voices from text and audio samples."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"However, concerns about the misuse of this technology have been raised, including the potential for scams and the creation of fake, multilingual human voices."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"A notable example of voice cloning technology being misused occurred in 2023 when ElevenLabs' software was used to generate a realistic voice of Emma Watson, leading to a viral incident."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"The technology has also been used in legitimate applications, such as by game developer Paradox Interactive, to enhance the realism of audio content."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"OpenAI has taken steps to address concerns about the misuse of its technology, including phasing out voice recognition for bank account verification and developing technologies to track audiovisual content."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"Voice cloning technology has raised legal and ethical implications, including concerns about privacy, intellectual property, and the potential for abuse."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"The technology has also been criticized for its potential to be used in scams, as demonstrated by a case in 2023 where a scammer used a cloned voice to extort money from a loved one."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"The development of voice cloning technology has sparked debates about the need for regulations and ethical guidelines, given the potential for misuse and the impact on society."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"Companies such as ElevenLabs and OpenAI have emphasized the importance of security measures and transparency in the development and use of voice cloning technology."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"The technology has also been used to create fake, multilingual human voices, raising concerns about its potential for abuse and the need for stricter regulations."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"The development of voice cloning technology has been driven by the need for more realistic and nuanced voices in various industries, including entertainment, accessibility, and customer service."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"Voice cloning technology has the potential to be used in education, such as creating personalized language learning materials, but its potential for misuse necessitates the implementation of strict regulations and safeguards."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"The technology's ability to generate realistic audio content can aid in language learning, but its potential for misuse, such as creating fake audio recordings of someone without their consent, raises significant ethical concerns."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"The importance of addressing the legal and ethical implications of voice cloning technology cannot be overstated, as it can be used for both beneficial and harmful purposes."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"The development of voice cloning technology has highlighted the need for a balanced approach, one that prioritizes both innovation and responsibility."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"Voice cloning technology has developed significantly, becoming increasingly realistic and accessible, raising both excitement and concern."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"It uses machine learning algorithms to simulate anyone\u2019s voice, requiring specific voice data to analyze and learn the unique patterns of an individual."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"Voice cloning tools are now available on the internet, allowing anyone to use them with no technical knowledge or cost."},{"citations":{"20185038-4ffa-4344-aaa9-bea225b8c6a5_636246971":1.0},"text":"ElevenLabs, a company developing speech cloning technology, offers a free and premium service to generate audio content for users."},{"citations":{"2018503