 compared to traditional computers.\nThe UAE aims to invest in quantum computing to enable innovation and a knowledge and sustainable economy through the Quantum Research Center and UAE institutes and universities to explore the future of this vital sector. The Institute of Technology Innovation \u2019 s (TII) Quantitative Research Center is working to build the first quantum computer in the UAE, according to the Interregional Center for Strategic Analytics in Abu Dhabi.\nThe UAE has quickly realized the benefits of the quantum computing sector in all sectors and fields, especially in the economy and scientific research, as part of the country \u2019 s long-term strategies to keep pace with the global technological development represented by the fourth industrial revolution and artificial intelligence, which will change the face of the world in the coming years.\nIDC expects global investments in quantum computing to reach $16.4 billion by the end of 2027, with a compound annual growth rate of 11.5%, which includes investments by the public and private sectors and R & D spending from technology, services and finance companies.\nThere is growing interest in quantum computing by global government agencies, with 14 of them (13 countries plus the European Union) announcing multi-year initiatives that will generate billions of dollars for quantum computing research.\nThe center said that the UAE is among the 50 projects working to create an attractive investment environment for investments in new and future sectors, including quantum computing technology.\nAccording to Accenture Middle East, quantum computing technology is advancing rapidly, making it a promising technology sector.\nThe US and China dominate the quantum computing sector to take advantage of the features of the new technological revolution that has enabled scientists to study the basic particles of matter, whose applications have multiplied across different fields despite their relative novelty, promising radical transformations for any industry dependent on speed and processing power, including aerospace, automotive, medicine and others.\nQuantum computing technologies have a huge market value, with quantum computing alone expected to reach a global market value of $1 trillion by 2035.\nQuantum technology has played a role in many areas, including complex mathematical models, simulations, electronic devices, CT scanners and many others, as it has the potential to revolutionize the way humans communicate and process information at record speeds.\nThe most prominent areas of use of quantum computing can be found in many fields of military, communications and medicine, and can address economic crises and challenges quickly, and there is no doubt that quantum computing technology can change the map of national industries.\nMajor technology companies are leading efforts to develop quantum computing, with Google Research Lab and IBM, which built one of the largest quantum computers in the field, and the Chinese University of Science and Technology has developed a quantum computer that is 10 billion times faster than the computer developed by Google.\nFollow the economic statement via Google News\nMENAFN24032024000110011019ID1108015991\nLegal Disclaimer:\nMENA Financial Services Network provides information \"as is\" without any representations or warranties...\nThis disclaims our responsibility for the privacy practices or content of the sites included in our network, including images and videos.\nFor any queries regarding the use and reuse of this source of information, please contact the provider of the above article.","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2024-0008.json.gz:12021","uncompressed_offset":398369350,"url":"menafn.com/arabic/1108015991/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%95%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%AA%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%AB%D9%85%D8%B1-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AD%D9%88%D8%B3%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%B4%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%81-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%82%D8%A8%D9%84","warc_date":"2024-03-24T23:10:01.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:401cd12a-6c4c-4c7c-9ca3-dcf526538f39>","warc_url":"https://menafn.com/arabic/1108015991/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%95%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%AA%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%AB%D9%85%D8%B1-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AD%D9%88%D8%B3%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%B4%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%81-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%82%D8%A8%D9%84"},"created":"2024-03-25T02:58:50.000Z","lang":"eng"},"9d67d90b-c58f-4444-aaaa-88164c533333_281634985":{"id":"9d67d90b-c58f-4444-aaaa-88164c533333_281634985","text":"Quantum Computing Market was valued at nearly USD 234.06 billion by 2032\n\nPrudour Private Limited\n\nUpdated \u00b7 Mar 06, 2023\n\nQuantum Computing Market Overview\n\nPublished Via 11Press: Quantum computing is a rapidly developing market that is revolutionizing how we approach computing and data processing. By employing principles of quantum mechanics to perform computations, quantum computers are capable of solving problems that classical computers may find impossible or impracticable to resolve.\n\nThe global\u00a0quantum computing\u00a0market size is forecast to reach\u00a0USD 234.06 billion\u00a0by 2032 from\u00a0USD 10.13 billion\u00a0in 2022, rising at a compound annual growth rate\u00a0(CAGR) of 36.89%\u00a0during the forecast period.\n\nAt present, the quantum computing market is dominated by a few major players such as IBM, Google, Microsoft, and Honeywell. These firms are investing heavily in quantum computing research and development as well as creating quantum computing hardware and software systems.\n\nThe quantum computing market is expected to have a profound effect on industries such as healthcare, finance, logistics, and energy. Some key applications of quantum computing include drug discovery, supply chain optimization, financial modeling, and climate modeling.\n\nThough the quantum computing market is promising, it still faces several obstacles such as high costs of hardware, a shortage of skilled experts in this area, and technical difficulties when building large-scale quantum computers. With ongoing research and development efforts, however, these problems should be overcome within the coming years, leading to even greater growth and innovation in this space.\n\nKey Takeaways\n\n  \u2022 The global quantum computing market size was valued at\u00a0USD 234.06 billion\u00a0in 2022 and is expected to grow at a\u00a0CAGR of around 36.89% from 2022 to 2032.\n  \u2022 Quantum computing is capable of solving problems that would be intractable or impossible for classical computers to solve.\n  \u2022 The quantum computing market is dominated by a few major players, including IBM, Google, Microsoft and Honeywell.\n  \u2022 The quantum computing market is expected to have a profound effect on numerous industries, such as healthcare, finance, logistics and energy.\n  \u2022 Quantum computing has many important applications such as drug discovery, supply chain optimization, financial modeling and climate modeling.\n  \u2022 The quantum computing market remains plagued by several obstacles, such as the high cost of quantum computing hardware, lack of qualified quantum computing experts and technical difficulties in building and running large-scale quantum computing systems.\n  \u2022 Research and development are expected to overcome these obstacles within the next couple of years, propelling even greater growth and innovation in the quantum computing market.\n\nRequest For Sample Report:\u00a0https://market.us/report/quantum-computing-market/request-sample/\n\nRegional Snapshot\n\n  \u2022 North America:\u00a0North America is currently the leading market for quantum computing, with the United States playing a major role. Major companies such as IBM, Google, and Microsoft are driving this growth through their presence and investment in research and development activities related to quantum computing. This region boasts numerous key players such as IBM, Google, and Microsoft which are driving demand within this region.\n  \u2022 Europe:\u00a0Europe is an increasingly important market for quantum computing, with countries such as the UK, Germany, and France investing heavily in research and development. Through partnerships between quantum computing companies and other technology firms as well as the growing adoption of quantum computing across various industries, this region\u2019s market is experiencing rapid expansion.\n  \u2022 Asia Pacific:\u00a0The quantum computing market in Asia Pacific is expected to experience significant growth over the coming years due to increased investments in research and development by countries like China, Japan, and South Korea. Furthermore, there have been an increasing number of collaborations between companies using quantum computing with academic institutions as well as its increasing adoption across industries like healthcare and finance \u2013 all contributing factors for market expansion within this region.\n  \u2022 The Rest of the World:\u00a0Countries such as Brazil, South Africa, and the UAE are expected to experience significant growth in the quantum computing market over the coming years due to increased investments in research and development efforts as well as the growing adoption of quantum computing across various industries. These factors are fueling this region\u2019s meteoric rise in this region.\n\nDrivers\n\n  \u2022 Quantum Computing Gaining Adoption in Various Industries:\u00a0Quantum computing is seeing an uptick in popularity across a range of industries, such as healthcare, finance, logistics, and energy \u2013 as companies seek to use their power to solve complex problems and gain an edge in competition.\n  \u2022 Investments in Quantum Computing Research and Development:\u00a0Governments, academic institutions, and private companies have made 