erships and Collaborations:\u00a0The growing number of partnerships and collaborations among quantum computing companies, other technology firms, academic institutions, and research organizations is creating opportunities for the development of new quantum computing hardware and software systems as well as its adoption across various industries.\n  \u2022 Advancements in Quantum Computing Hardware and Software:\u00a0With the rapid progress being made in the development of quantum computing hardware and software, new opportunities will present themselves for applying this technology across various industries and fields.\n  \u2022 The growing availability of cloud-based quantum computing services:\u00a0Cloud-based quantum computing services are making it simpler for companies and researchers to access and utilize quantum computing technology, spurring adoption and innovation within the field.\n  \u2022 Growth of Quantum Computing as a Service:\u00a0As more companies and researchers embrace the potential of quantum computing, cloud-based quantum computing services are creating exciting new business opportunities for those offering these solutions.\n  \u2022 Potential for Breakthroughs in Areas such as Drug Discovery, Finance, and Energy:\u00a0Quantum computing holds the potential to unravel complex issues in fields like drug discovery, finance, and energy \u2013 leading to major breakthroughs and advances. This presents companies with unique opportunities for those who can develop and implement quantum computing solutions in these sectors.\n\nChallenges\n\n  \u2022 Technical Challenges in Constructing and Running Large Quantum Computing Systems:\u00a0As quantum computing systems continue to emerge, numerous technical obstacles must be overcome such as noise reduction, error correction, and scalability. These issues make it challenging for companies to construct and run these massive quantum computers efficiently.\n  \u2022 Limited Access to Qualified Quantum Computing Experts:\u00a0There is currently a shortage of highly experienced quantum computing professionals, making it difficult for companies to construct and maintain quantum computing systems. This shortage could potentially restrict the growth of this industry in the coming years.\n  \u2022 Quantum computing Applications:\u00a0While quantum computing has many potential uses, the number of practical applications that have been created and implemented remains limited. This could make investing in quantum computing technology and research on practical applications an attractive prospect.\n\nGrow your profit margin with Market.us\u00a0Get this Report\n\nRecent Developments\n\n  \u2022 Google Claims Quantum Supremacy:\u00a0In 2019, Google claimed to have achieved quantum supremacy by performing a calculation on its quantum computer that even the most powerful supercomputers would take thousands of years to complete. This was seen as an important milestone in the advancement of quantum computing technology.\n  \u2022 IBM Launches Quantum Computing Program for Students:\u00a0In 2020, IBM unveiled a quantum computing program specifically tailored towards students that provides them with access to IBM\u2019s resources and tools, as well as a platform for learning and collaboration.\n  \u2022 Honeywell Achieves Quantum Computer Record Performance:\u00a0On March 20, 2021, Honeywell revealed its creation of a quantum computer with an astonishing quantum volume of 512. This feat marked an amazing advancement in quantum computing technology and demonstrated how rapidly progress has been made since then.\n  \u2022 Amazon Web Services Announces Quantum Computing Service:\u00a0On June 2021, Amazon Web Services (AWS) announced the launch of its own quantum computing service called Amazon Bracket. This offering gives customers access to various vendors\u2019 hardware as well as tools and resources for developing and testing quantum algorithms.\n\nKey Market Segments\n\nType\n\n  \u2022 Hardware\n  \u2022 Software\n  \u2022 Services\n\nApplication\n\n  \u2022 Defense\n  \u2022 Healthcare & pharmaceuticals\n  \u2022 Chemicals\n  \u2022 Banking & Finance\n  \u2022 Energy & power\n\nKey Market Players\n\n  \u2022 D-Wave Systems\n  \u2022 Google\n  \u2022 IBM\n  \u2022 Intel\n  \u2022 Microsoft\n  \u2022 1QB Information Technologies\n  \u2022 Anyon Systems\n  \u2022 Cambridge Quantum Computing\n  \u2022 ID Quantique\n  \u2022 IonQ\n  \u2022 QbitLogic\n  \u2022 QC Ware\n  \u2022 Quantum Circuits\n  \u2022 Qubitekk\n  \u2022 QxBranch\n  \u2022 Rigetti Computing\n\nNature Insights\n\n  \u2022 Progress is being made in the development of quantum computing hardware:\u00a0Despite the challenges facing large-scale quantum computing systems, progress is being made on quantum computing hardware. This includes creating quantum processors with increasingly more qubits and creating new materials suitable for use in quantum computers.\n  \u2022 Quantum computing software is still in its early stages:\u00a0While progress is being made with quantum computing hardware, software development for quantum computation remains at a standstill. This presents an immense challenge to the industry as developing efficient quantum algorithms is essential to realizing its full potential.\n  \u2022 Collaboration is essential to the advancement of quantum computing:\u00a0Collaboration between companies, academic institutions, and research organizations is essential for progress in this industry. This includes joint efforts to develop new hardware and software systems as well as collaborations that promote quantum computing across various industries.\n\nReport Scope\n\nReport Attribute Details\nThe market size value in 2022 USD 10.13 Bn\nRevenue forecast by 2032 USD 234.6 Bn\nGrowth Rate CAGR Of 36.89%\nRegions Covered North America, Europe, Asia Pacific, Latin America, and Middle East & Africa, and the Rest of the World\nHistorical Years 2017-2022\nBase Year 2022\nEstimated Year 2023\nShort-Term Projection Year 2028\nLong-Term Projected Year 2032\n\nContact us\n\nContact Person: Mr. Lawrence John\n\nMarket.us (Powered By Prudour Pvt. Ltd.)\n\nTel: +1 718 618 4351\n\nSend Email: [email\u00a0protected]\n\nFAQ.\n\nWhat is quantum computing?\n\nQuantum computing is a type of processing data using quantum mechanics. It relies on principles such as superposition, entanglement, and interference which enable quantum computers to perform calculations that would be impossible with classical computers.\n\nWhat are some potential applications of quantum computing?\n\nQuantum computing holds great promise for revolutionizing industries such as drug discovery, finance, energy, and logistics. Potential uses include creating new drugs and materials, optimizing supply chains and logistics networks, and even improving weather forecasting models with greater precision.\n\nWhat are some of the challenges facing the quantum computing market?\n\nThe quantum computing market faces numerous obstacles, such as technical difficulties in building and running large-scale quantum computers, high costs associated with quantum computing hardware, a scarcity of highly qualified quantum experts, and an absence of practical applications developed and deployed.\n\nWho are some of the major players in the quantum computing market?\n\nMajor companies operating within this space include IBM, Google, Microsoft, Honeywell, Intel, and Rigetti Computing. These firms are actively developing and commercializing quantum computing hardware and software systems.\n\nWhat is the outlook for the quantum computing market?\n\nOverall, analysts anticipate a bright future for quantum computing, with continued investment and innovation anticipated in the coming years. Though still in its early stages of development, its potential advantages are immense - leading to rapid industry growth over the coming years.\n\nPrudour Private Limited\n\nThe team behind market.us, marketresearch.biz, market.biz and more. Our purpose is to keep our customers ahead of the game with regard to the markets. They may fluctuate up or down, but we will help you to stay ahead of the curve in these market fluctuations. Our consistent growth and ability to deliver in-depth analyses and market insight has engaged genuine market players. They have faith in us to offer the data and information they require to make balanced and decisive marketing decisions.","url":"https://www.enterpriseappstoday.com/news/quantum-computing-market-was-valued-at-nearly-usd-234-06-billion-by-2032.html"},"9b9f8be2-d6b8-4d95-9482-f8415bab065b_399146656":{"id":"9b9f8be2-d6b8-4d95-9482-f8415bab065b_399146656","text":"Investments in quantum computing startups reached $2.35 billion in 2022\nQuantum technologies have great potential for both science and business, and attract large investments in different countries of the world, including Russia.\nThis is stated in the analytical report \"Quantum Computing: Prospects for Business\", which was prepared jointly with the Federal State Unitary Enterprise \"VNIIA named after N.L. Dukhov\" and the Institute of Artificial Intelligence AIRI.\n\u201cIncreasing attention in the world is paid to supporting start-ups in the field of quantum technologies.\nIn 2022, venture investors around the world invested $2.35 billion in them.\nAlso last year, almost 1,600 patents were issued and published in all subfields of quantum computing: from physical implementations of quantum equipment and error correction to AI [artificial intelligence] and machine learning.\nVideo of the day\nLeading countries, realizing the breakthrough potential of this direction, include quantum technologies in national programs and allocate increasing budgets for research.\nThe leader is China with $15.3 billion in government funding.\nDevelopment programs have the leading technological corporations of the world.\nSo, which has made a quantum processor for 433 qubits [qubit or quantum bit - the main unit of information in quantum processors and quantum computing], plans this year to increase the number of qubits to 1121, and intends to show a device for a thousand qubits after 2025.\nThe intention to develop a full stack of technologies for quantum computing announced and has already released to the market quantum chips on spin qubits.\nIn Russia, work on quantum computing is underway on four key physical platforms: superconducting qubits, photonic circuits, neutral atoms, and trapped ions.\nThe Russian Federation has also formed a pool of organizations, including companies, scientific institutions and universities that conduct research and development, study the applicability of quantum computing to practical tasks.\n\u201cQuantum computing can give the world an impetus to the development of new industries based on the processing of big data.\nIn addition, they can improve the performance and efficiency of artificial intelligence algorithms, the accuracy of models and simulations of complex systems (such as molecules of new drugs, chemical reactions or physical processes), as well as provide a new level of calculations in finance and logistics, new solutions to climate problems and cryptographic algorithms that will provide a higher level of security.\nThe authors of the report come to the conclusion that although no one in the world has been able to demonstrate practical quantum superiority, nevertheless, companies should plan today what will happen after its achievement.\nQuantum computing is able to integrate seamlessly into data processing workflows, using adaptation tools for popular programming languages and interfaces.","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2023-0027.json.gz:171094","uncompressed_offset":399146656,"url":"finance.rambler.ru/economics/51460047-investitsii-v-startapy-sfery-kvantovyh-vychisleniy-v-2022-godu-dostigli-2-35-mlrd/","warc_date":"2023-09-21T14:34:01.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:9b9f8be2-d6b8-4d95-9482-f8415bab065b>","warc_url":"https://finance.rambler.ru/economics/51460047-investitsii-v-startapy-sfery-kvantovyh-vychisleniy-v-2022-godu-dostigli-2-35-mlrd/"},"created":"2023-09-21T14:46:42.000Z","lang":"eng"}}}
