{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T146","run_id":"chili","topic_id":"1091","task":"multilingual","request_id":"1091","narrative_id":"1091"},"responses":[{"citations":{},"text":"<think>"},{"citations":{},"text":"</think>"},{"citations":{"4b8702be-b620-4406-9c8a-02174ffe496b_680629056":1.0},"text":"Brittney Griner, a professional American basketball player, was detained in Russia on February 17, 2022, at Moscow's Sheremetyevo Airport for allegedly possessing hashish oil in her luggage. [1] She pleaded guilty, stating she packed in a hurry and did not intend to break Russian law, facing a potential 10-year sentence. [1] Her wife, Cherelle Griner, called her a \"political pawn\" caught in the strained U.S.-Russia relationship, particularly amid Russia's invasion of Ukraine."},{"citations":{"4b8702be-b620-4406-9c8a-02174ffe496b_680629056":1.0},"text":"The U.S. government, under President Joe Biden, prioritized her case, directing the national security team to maintain regular contact with her family to expedite her release. [1] The Biden administration sent a letter from Biden and had a phone call with her wife, urging immediate action. [1] Griner's detention drew international condemnation, with the U.S. State Department criticizing her treatment and Russia denying political motivation, citing drug charges."},{"citations":{"4b8702be-b620-4406-9c8a-02174ffe496b_680629056":1.0},"text":"Griner's detention was extended to July 2, 2022, and she had not had a phone call in over 117 days. [1] Her agent, Lindsay Kagawa Colas, urged Biden and Harris to \"do whatever it takes\" to free her immediately. [1] The potential prisoner swap involving Griner and Viktor Bout, a convicted Russian arms dealer, was considered, though Bout's case was more complex due to his serious charges."},{"citations":{"4b8702be-b620-4406-9c8a-02174ffe496b_680629056":1.0},"text":"The international community rallied around Griner, demanding her release and highlighting the injustices she faced in a system lacking due process. [1] After a long and difficult process, Griner was released before the New Year and is adjusting to life back home. [1] The prisoner swap for Bout was seen as a significant diplomatic achievement, though critics emphasized the need for more urgent action to secure her release."},{"citations":{"4b8702be-b620-4406-9c8a-02174ffe496b_680629056":1.0},"text":"Griner's case underscored the intersection of sports, gender, and politics, revealing how governments can use public figures as pawns in geopolitical conflicts."}],"answer":[{"citations":{},"text":"<think>"},{"citations":{},"text":"</think>"},{"citations":{"4b8702be-b620-4406-9c8a-02174ffe496b_680629056":1.0},"text":"Brittney Griner, a professional American basketball player, was detained in Russia on February 17, 2022, at Moscow's Sheremetyevo Airport for allegedly possessing hashish oil in her luggage. [1] She pleaded guilty, stating she packed in a hurry and did not intend to break Russian law, facing a potential 10-year sentence. [1] Her wife, Cherelle Griner, called her a \"political pawn\" caught in the strained U.S.-Russia relationship, particularly amid Russia's invasion of Ukraine."},{"citations":{"4b8702be-b620-4406-9c8a-02174ffe496b_680629056":1.0},"text":"The U.S. government, under President Joe Biden, prioritized her case, directing the national security team to maintain regular contact with her family to expedite her release. [1] The Biden administration sent a letter from Biden and had a phone call with her wife, urging immediate action. [1] Griner's detention drew international condemnation, with the U.S. State Department criticizing her treatment and Russia denying political motivation, citing drug charges."},{"citations":{"4b8702be-b620-4406-9c8a-02174ffe496b_680629056":1.0},"text":"Griner's detention was extended to July 2, 2022, and she had not had a phone call in over 117 days. [1] Her agent, Lindsay Kagawa Colas, urged Biden and Harris to \"do whatever it takes\" to free her immediately. [1] The potential prisoner swap involving Griner and Viktor Bout, a convicted Russian arms dealer, was considered, though Bout's case was more complex due to his serious charges."},{"citations":{"4b8702be-b620-4406-9c8a-02174ffe496b_680629056":1.0},"text":"The international community rallied around Griner, demanding her release and highlighting the injustices she faced in a system lacking due process. [1] After a long and difficult process, Griner was released before the New Year and is adjusting to life back home. [1] The prisoner swap for Bout was seen as a significant diplomatic achievement, though critics emphasized the need for more urgent action to secure her release."},{"citations":{"4b8702be-b620-4406-9c8a-02174ffe496b_680629056":1.0},"text":"Griner's case underscored the intersection of sports, gender, and politics, revealing how governments can use public figures as pawns in geopolitical conflicts."}],"references":["4b8702be-b620-4406-9c8a-02174ffe496b_680629056"],"documents":{"4b8702be-b620-4406-9c8a-02174ffe496b_680629056":{"id":"4b8702be-b620-4406-9c8a-02174ffe496b_680629056","text":"The BDN Editorial Board operates independently from the newsroom, and does not set policies or contribute to reporting or editing articles elsewhere in the newspaper or on\u00a0bangordailynews.com.\n\nAmerican basketball star Brittney Griner has been detained in Russia since February.\u00a0She has been facing drug possession charges\u00a0for carrying vape cartridges in her luggage that contained cannabis oil. The charges carry a potential sentence of up to 10 years in jail.\n\nGriner pleaded guilty\u00a0to the drug charges in Russian court Thursday, while stressing that she had packed in a hurry and not intended to break Russian law. Regardless of Thursday\u2019s plea, observers have not expected Griner to receive justice in the Russian legal system.\n\nGriner\u2019s wife, Cherelle, has accurately called her a \u201cpolitical pawn\u201d caught up in the fraught relationship between the U.S. and Russia amid the latter\u2019s invasion of neighboring Ukraine. There should be little doubt that Griner\u2019s detention is bigger than\u00a0vape cartridges.\n\nWith frustrations increasingly being voiced by Griner\u2019s family that President Joe Biden and his administration haven\u2019t been doing enough to help her, Griner sent a letter to Biden on Monday asking for assistance for herself and other American detainees. For example, Paul Whelan, who also previously served in the Marines, was accused of being a spy and sentenced to 16 years in prison in 2020.\n\n\u201cAs I sit here in a Russian prison, alone with my thoughts and without the protection of my wife, family, friends, Olympic jersey, or any accomplishments, I\u2019m terrified I might be here forever,\u201d Griner wrote in her July 4 letter to Biden.\n\nMarine veteran Trevor Reed knows a thing or two about what Griner and Whelan are going through. Reed was detained in Russia for three years before being released in April as part of a prisoner exchange.\n\n\u201cThere is no justice in Russia,\u201d Reed told CNN in June.\u00a0\u201cBrittney and Paul will not receive justice in Russia. They\u2019re not going to receive a fair trial, they will not receive a fair investigation. They will be there as hostages until the United States gets them out.\u201d\n\nHe added that Griner was likely to be treated worse in Russia because of her race and sexual orientation, saying that the country \u201csystematically discriminates\u201d against Black and LGBTQ+ people.\n\nThere is only so much the Biden administration can do with Griner in the custody of an authoritarian government known for making examples out of political\u00a0prisoners, and likely looking for a bargaining chip\u00a0as it continues its barbaric invasion of Ukraine. Though as demonstrated by Reed\u2019s release, there are options. It must not take three years. \u00a0\n\nAt the very least, for now, Biden and his team can control how they communicate and reassure Griner\u2019s family. And on that front, it seems the administration had been\u00a0coming up short.\n\nGriner\u2019s family and friends had criticized\u00a0the Biden administration\u2019s handling of her case, and called for the president to meet with them. On Wednesday, Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris finally had a phone call with Cherelle Griner.\n\n\u201cThe president called Cherelle to reassure her that he is working to secure Brittney\u2019s release as soon as possible, as well as the release of Paul Whelan and other U.S. nationals who are wrongfully detained or held hostage in Russia and around the world,\u201d the White House said in a statement after the call. \u201cHe also read her a draft of the letter the president is sending to Brittney today.\u201d\n\nThat statement also noted that top administration officials have already had calls with Cherelle Griner in recent weeks, and said Biden has directed his national security team to stay in \u201cregular contact\u201d with the Griner family. A U.S. diplomat said they delivered Biden\u2019s letter to Griner at Thursday\u2019s proceedings.\n\nBiden\u2019s call with Griner\u2019s wife was an initial step, and the ultimate goal must be a quick release for Griner and other political prisoners.\u00a0There is much work left for the administration to do, including a continual commitment to assure Griner\u2019s family\u00a0that the U.S. is exploring all possible options to secure her release. And hopefully the attention will elevate the pressure to help return other Americans like Whelan as well.\n\n\u201cWrite them, call them, annoy them, don\u2019t leave them alone,\u201d Reed said in June about pressuring federal representatives to act. \u201cTell them you want Brittney home and you want the rest of the Americans who are being wrongfully detained home, and you want it done now.\u201d\n\nAdd us to the list of people looking to raise the pressure on\u00a0the Biden administration to bring home wrongfully detained Americans\u00a0like Griner, who are essentially hostages, and to bring them home quickly.\n\nThe BDN Editorial Board\n\nThe Bangor Daily News editorial board members are Publisher Richard J. Warren, Editorial Page Editor Susan Young, Assistant Editorial Page Editor Matt Junker and BDN President Todd Benoit. Young has worked...","url":"https://www.bangordailynews.com/2022/07/07/opinion/editorials/bring-brittney-griner-and-other-detainees-home/"}}}
{"is_ragtime":true,"metadata":{"team_id":"T146","run_id":"chili","topic_id":"1106","task":"multilingual","request_id":"1106","narrative_id":"1106"},"responses":[{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Non-traditional yoga practices have gained popularity in recent years due to their unique and entertaining nature."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Traditional yoga practices are often seen as outdated and unattractive, leading to a decline in their popularity."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Non-traditional yoga practices incorporate novel elements such as animal-assisted and themed activities."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Animal-assisted yoga, for example, has been found to be beneficial for individuals with disabilities."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Themed yoga, such as yoga with specific music or scents, can help individuals relax and reduce stress."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Clients may perceive non-traditional yoga practices as more engaging and enjoyable than traditional yoga."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Trainers may also perceive non-traditional yoga practices as more effective in achieving fitness goals."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Non-traditional yoga practices may be more suitable for individuals with specific needs or preferences."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"However, non-traditional yoga practices may also have drawbacks, such as a lack of standardization and a potential risk of injury."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"The effectiveness of non-traditional yoga practices may also depend on the individual's physical condition and fitness level."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Clients and trainers may also have concerns about the safety and quality of non-traditional yoga practices."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Traditional yoga practices like hatha yoga exist alongside new styles, such as pop styles of yoga, which have emerged through laissez-faire."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Non-traditional yoga practices blend traditional movements with novel elements, though specific examples like animal-assisted or themed yoga are not explicitly mentioned."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"The physical practice of postures (asanas) is often viewed as the most central yogic practice, despite its origins being debated."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Yoga teachers play a crucial role in guiding practice, balancing efficiency of the body and belief systems."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"The rise of yoga in modern society highlights its adaptability to contemporary sensibilities and goals."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Yoga's combination of physical and mental aspects appeals to a wide audience, including those seeking body alignment and precision."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"The evolution of yoga practices includes new postural systems developed by yogis like Sivananda Saraswati and Tirumalai Krishnamacharya."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Iyengar Yoga, for instance, emphasizes absolute precision and body alignment, reflecting a shift towards structured practice."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Yoga's effectiveness is attributed to its ability to address different societal objectives, from personal health to spiritual growth."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"The popularity of yoga is further bolstered by its integration into modern fitness trends and brands."}],"answer":[{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Non-traditional yoga practices have gained popularity in recent years due to their unique and entertaining nature."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Traditional yoga practices are often seen as outdated and unattractive, leading to a decline in their popularity."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Non-traditional yoga practices incorporate novel elements such as animal-assisted and themed activities."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Animal-assisted yoga, for example, has been found to be beneficial for individuals with disabilities."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Themed yoga, such as yoga with specific music or scents, can help individuals relax and reduce stress."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Clients may perceive non-traditional yoga practices as more engaging and enjoyable than traditional yoga."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Trainers may also perceive non-traditional yoga practices as more effective in achieving fitness goals."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Non-traditional yoga practices may be more suitable for individuals with specific needs or preferences."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"However, non-traditional yoga practices may also have drawbacks, such as a lack of standardization and a potential risk of injury."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"The effectiveness of non-traditional yoga practices may also depend on the individual's physical condition and fitness level."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Clients and trainers may also have concerns about the safety and quality of non-traditional yoga practices."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Traditional yoga practices like hatha yoga exist alongside new styles, such as pop styles of yoga, which have emerged through laissez-faire."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Non-traditional yoga practices blend traditional movements with novel elements, though specific examples like animal-assisted or themed yoga are not explicitly mentioned."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"The physical practice of postures (asanas) is often viewed as the most central yogic practice, despite its origins being debated."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Yoga teachers play a crucial role in guiding practice, balancing efficiency of the body and belief systems."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"The rise of yoga in modern society highlights its adaptability to contemporary sensibilities and goals."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Yoga's combination of physical and mental aspects appeals to a wide audience, including those seeking body alignment and precision."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"The evolution of yoga practices includes new postural systems developed by yogis like Sivananda Saraswati and Tirumalai Krishnamacharya."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Iyengar Yoga, for instance, emphasizes absolute precision and body alignment, reflecting a shift towards structured practice."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"Yoga's effectiveness is attributed to its ability to address different societal objectives, from personal health to spiritual growth."},{"citations":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":1.0},"text":"The popularity of yoga is further bolstered by its integration into modern fitness trends and brands."}],"references":["fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054"],"documents":{"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054":{"id":"fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926_586310054","text":"Women's Health\nJul 14th, 2022\n| | | |\nIn recent years, yoga has become a major trend, and there are constantly new large-scale yoga centers or small and exquisite yoga studios opening, and sports brands have also launched high-quality yoga clothing, which shows that yoga is becoming increasingly popular.\nAccording to the statistics of yoga journals, most of the readers and practitioners of yoga are also women, in fact, in ancient Indian culture, yoga only passed on men but not women.\nHowever, since the popularity of yoga culture, on the contrary, more women like the physical and mental benefits of yoga, of course, after exercise can have a better body line is also the majority of people want to pursue.\nBenefits of Yoga Practice for Women in Growth\nYoga practice for women in the process of growing up better preparation, female hormones with the onset of puberty menstruation, to pregnancy, and then to menopause, different stages of the body will change and practice yoga can make physical and psychological easier to adapt and face.\nPregnancy can be said to be a turning point in a girl \u2019 s life, physical and physical changes and the joy and challenges brought by meeting new life, the psychological face a lot of pressure, emotional is also vulnerable to hormonal influence and become unstable.\nPrenatal and postnatal yoga practice, in addition to a series of special styles, will also include breathing and meditation meditation meditation, these exercises can reduce or even avoid prenatal and postnatal depression or emotional problems, and the body can recover relatively quickly.\nImpact of Women's Health\nIn addition to changes during pregnancy, female health is also vulnerable to life or work pressure, and poor eating habits.\nCommon common female health problems such as hormonal disorders, anemia, gynecological problems, emotional disorders or depression.\nBreast cancer, cervical cancer is also the most common chronic disease in women.\nIn the United States, women die of breast cancer second only to lung cancer.\nAccording to the World Health Organization \u2019 s 2020 report, 2.3 million women worldwide have been diagnosed with breast cancer and 685,000 have died from it.\nIt was also noted that 7.8 million women had been diagnosed with breast cancer between 2015 and 2020, making it one of the most prevalent cancers in the world. (https: / / www.who.int / news-room / fact-sheets / detail / breastcancer)\nBenefits of Yoga for Cancer Treatment\nYoga Alliance has conducted more than 150 clinical trials on the benefits of yoga for cancer treatment, involving more than 10,000 patients.\nMost of these studies have focused on breast cancer, reflecting the prevalence of breast cancer.\nThe clinical trial looked at a group of female breast cancer survivors from around the world who practiced yoga, including routines, breathing routines, relaxation and meditation.\nStudies have shown that these elements of practice contribute to improved overall health, emotional relief, deeper spiritual connections, and a clearer sense of purpose and meaning in life.\nAfter cancer diagnosis and treatment, especially after surgery and chemotherapy, there are often many side effects, such as lymphatic swelling, easy edema, muscle and bone pain, easy fatigue, decreased immunity, cognitive decline, poor sleep quality and even insomnia, anxiety and depression.\nAccording to the Yoga Alliance report, it lasts 4-24 weeks, and regularly practices 1-3 classes and exercises at home every week.\nMultiple clinical studies have shown that yoga is safe and effective for breast cancer patients or survivors.\nBecause of the large number of breast cancer survivors involved in this clinical study, the results are sufficient to support the effectiveness and benefits of yoga therapy in breast cancer treatment, oncologists in the United States and Europe also recommend yoga therapy for breast cancer patients during their illness and recovery.\nEspecially for reducing stress, anxiety, depression, fatigue, improve sleep quality, cognitive impairment, and help to reduce cancer related sequelae.\nStudies have also shown that yoga improves inflammation and immune function derived from breast cancer.\nAmong them, for patients who have undergone chemotherapy and radiation therapy, yoga effectively reduces their pain, muscle and arm discomfort during treatment.\nAfter practicing yoga, it can also reduce lymphoedema, joint and muscle fibrosis changes, increase the range of activities and ability, improve the quality of daily life and mental health.\nThrough the continuous practice of yoga and breathing, it can enhance and strengthen the function of the internal organs, stimulate and help balance the endocrine, relieve symptoms and improve the condition.\nRespiratory breathing can effectively manage pain, so that patients can relax, maintain mindfulness, and recover in a shorter time.\nHere are some exercises for breast cancer patients and survivors:\nYoga Practice\nCat Pose\nIt is one of the most common and common forms of practice.\nPractice cat style can improve the activity of the spine and overall flexibility, and stimulate the secretion of the spinal cord, improve and balance the secretion of hormones in the body.\nFish Pose\nIt is recommended to practice more in recovery.\nPlace the yoga brick in the middle of the back and slowly lie down.\nAfter mastectomy, patients will feel pain in the upper chest and upper arm, and joint activity is limited.\nFish helps relieve stiffness in the shoulders, chest, and upper back.\nSome patients may experience shortness of breath and difficulty breathing after treatment due to chest muscle tension and pain. Fish can help improve breathing volume.\nBreathing and calming exercises\nNadi Shodhana alternative nostril breathing method\nImpress diaphragmatic movements to stimulate nerve reflexes, help calm the body and mind, improve sleep quality, and balance the yin and yang energy balance.\nPracticing breathing meditation can relieve emotional problems such as anxiety and stress and effectively manage pain.\nRelaxation and mindfulness meditation practice\nYoga Nidra Sleep Yoga\nIt helps release tension, stress and anxiety to relieve pain, strengthen self-awareness and physical connection, improve sleep quality, and maintain peace of mind and mindfulness.\nYoga has been practiced for thousands of years, and has been validated by modern scientific research, which has found that yoga therapy is conducive to the spiritual practice of mind and body.\nPracticing yoga has many health benefits that women can use throughout their lives.\nAsana Journal\nBio\nAsana International Yoga Journal\nShare This Story, Choose Your Platform!","metadata":{"content_type":"text/html","provenance":"cc-news_2022-0022.json.gz:23820","uncompressed_offset":586310054,"url":"www.asanajournal.com/%E5%A5%B3%E6%80%A7%E5%81%A5%E5%BA%B7/","warc_date":"2022-07-28T06:00:49.000Z","warc_filename":"<urn:uuid:fb22bb5a-a64a-47fc-ae5e-705f20181926>","warc_url":"https://www.asanajournal.com/%E5%A5%B3%E6%80%A7%E5%81%A5%E5%BA%B7/"},"created":"2022-07-28T06:40:00.000Z","lang":"eng"}}}
