nnually."},{"citations":{"3c29e522-5c23-4b52-88ad-d09ae0ea9bf4_378764971":1.0},"text":"The income gap between MLM workers and non-workers is substantial, with workers earning up to 80% less than non-workers."},{"citations":{"3c29e522-5c23-4b52-88ad-d09ae0ea9bf4_378764971":1.0},"text":"MLM companies are more attractive to younger individuals and women, with 84% of workers being between 18 and 34 years old."},{"citations":{"3c29e522-5c23-4b52-88ad-d09ae0ea9bf4_378764971":1.0},"text":"The appeal of MLM companies varies by region, with higher attractiveness in countries like Brazil and China."},{"citations":{"3c29e522-5c23-4b52-88ad-d09ae0ea9bf4_378764971":1.0},"text":"China has strict government regulations on MLM companies, leading to closures and shifts to direct sales models."},{"citations":{"3c29e522-5c23-4b52-88ad-d09ae0ea9bf4_378764971":1.0},"text":"The Chinese government has prohibited pyramid schemes and banned high-commission sales models, affecting the MLM industry."},{"citations":{"3c29e522-5c23-4b52-88ad-d09ae0ea9bf4_378764971":1.0},"text":"MLM companies in China have experienced a decline in popularity due to regulatory changes and increased scrutiny."},{"citations":{"3c29e522-5c23-4b52-88ad-d09ae0ea9bf4_378764971":1.0},"text":"The appeal of MLM companies is also influenced by the level of economic development and social support in a given region."},{"citations":{"3c29e522-5c23-4b52-88ad-d09ae0ea9bf4_378764971":1.0},"text":"MLM companies are more attractive to individuals with lower levels of education, as they often require less formal training and have fewer entry barriers."},{"citations":{"3c29e522-5c23-4b52-88ad-d09ae0ea9bf4_378764971":1.0},"text":"The appeal of MLM companies is also influenced by cultural factors, with some communities being more receptive to the business model than others."},{"citations":{"3c29e522-5c23-4b52-88ad-d09ae0ea9bf4_378764971":1.0},"text":"The MLM industry has been a topic of controversy, with critics arguing that it often 